B040C001V001	40	1	1	The book of the generation of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham was the father of Isaac; Isaac was the father of Jacob;  Jacob, of Judah and his brethren;
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah (by Tamar), of Perez and Zerah; Perez, of Hezron; Hezron, of Ram;
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Ram, of Amminadab; Amminadab, of Nahshon; Nahshon, of Salmon;
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon (by Rahab), of Boaz; Boaz (by Ruth), of Obed; Obed, of Jesse;
B040C001V006	40	1	6	And Jesse, of David the king. David (by Uriahs widow), was the father of Solomon;
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon, of Rehoboam; Rehoboam, of Abijah; Abijah, of Asa;
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa, of Jehoshaphat; Jehoshaphat, of Joram; Joram, of Uzziah;
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah, of Jotham; Jotham, of Ahaz; Ahaz, of Hezekiah;
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah, of Manasseh; Manasseh, of Amon; Amon, of Josiah;
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah, of Jechoniah and his brethren, at the time of the carrying away to Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the carrying away into Babylon, Jechoniah became the father of Shealtiel; Shealtiel, of Zerubbabel;
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel, of Abiud; Abiud, of Eliakim; Eliakim, of Azor;
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor, of Sadoc; Sadoc, of Achim; Achim, of Eliud;
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud, of Eleazar; Eleazar, of Matthan; Matthan, of Jacob;
B040C001V016	40	1	16	And Jacob, of Joseph, the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus,  who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So the whole number of generations from Abraham to David is fourteen; from David to the exile to Babylon is fourteen; and from the exile to Babylon to Christ is fourteen.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	The birth of Jesus Christ took place in this way. After his mother,  Mary, had been betrothed to Joseph, before they came together, she was found to be with child by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	But Joseph her husband, because he was just a man and unwilling to disgrace her, was minded to put her away secretly.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	And while he was having this in mind, behold! an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	"Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary your wife home,  for what is begotten in her is by the Holy Spirit; and she will bear a son, and you are to call him Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins."
B040C001V022	40	1	22	All this happened that the word of the Lord spoken through the prophet might be fulfilled.
B040C001V023	40	1	23	Behold! the virgin shall be with child, and shall bear a son; and they shall call his name Immanuel, a word which means "God with us."
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Now when Joseph awoke from his sleep he did as the angel of the Lord had directed him, and took his wife home,
B040C001V025	40	1	25	but did not live with her until after the birth of her son, whom he called Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	After the birth of Jesus, which took place at Bethlehem in Judea,  during the reign of King Herod, lo! certain Magi arrived in Jerusalem, saying.
B040C002V002	40	2	2	"Where is the new-born King of the Jews? For we have seen his star in the East, and are come to worship him."
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When King Herod heard this he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	So when he had gathered together all the chief priests and rabbis of the people, he began to inquire of them where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	And they told him. "At Bethlehem in Judea, as it is written in the prophet.
B040C002V006	40	2	6	"And thou Bethlehem in the land of Judah, Thou are not least among the princes of Judah, For out of thee shall come a ruler Who shall shepherd my people, Israel."
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Thereupon Herod sent secretly for the Magi, and found out from them the time when the star appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	Then he sent them to Bethlehem, saying, "Go and make careful inquiry about the child, and as soon as you have found him bring me word,  that I, too, may go and worship him."
B040C002V009	40	2	9	The Magi listened to the king, and went on their way, and lo! the star which they had seen in the east led them until it came and stood over the place where the young child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	And when they saw the star, they rejoiced with great gladness.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	When they had entered the house, they saw the child with Mary, his mother, and opening their treasure-chests they gave him gifts, gold and frankincense and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	But because they were forbidden by God in a dream to go back to Herod, they returned to their own country by another route.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	When they were gone an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, saying; "Rise! Take the young child and his mother and flee into Egypt, and there remain until I bring you word; for Herod intends to make a search for the child, in order to put him to death."
B040C002V014	40	2	14	So Joseph arose, took the child and his mother, by night, and departed to Egypt.
B040C002V015	40	2	15	There he remained until the death of Herod, in order that the word of the Lord through the prophet might be fulfilled, which says, Out of Egypt I called my son.
B040C002V016	40	2	16	As soon as Herod saw that he had been mocked by the Magi, he was furious. He sent and put to death all the boys in Bethlehem and all the neighborhood who were two years old or under, in accordance with the date which he had ascertained from the Magi.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then were fulfilled the words spoken through Jeremiah, the prophet,  saying,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	A voice was heard in Ramah, Weeping and lamentation- Rachel weeping for her children, Inconsolable, because they were no more!
B040C002V019	40	2	19	But after Herods death an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	saying, "Rise! Take the child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel, for those who were seeking the life of the child are dead."
B040C002V021	40	2	21	So he rose and took the child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Archelaus was reigning in Judea in place of his father, Herod, he was afraid to go there; and being warned of God in a dream, he withdrew into Galilee and settled in a town called Nazareth,
B040C002V023	40	2	23	in fulfillment of the word spoken through the Prophets, He shall be called a Nazarene.
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In those days came John the Baptist preaching in the desert of Judea;
B040C003V002	40	3	2	"Repent," said he, "for the kingdom of heaven is at hand."
B040C003V003	40	3	3	This Johnit was of whom it was said through Isaiah, the prophet, The voice of one who cries aloud in the desert, "Prepare a way for the Lord, Make the paths straight for him."
B040C003V004	40	3	4	This Johnwore a garment of camels hair, and a leather belt around his waist, and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then Jerusalem began to go out to him, and all Judea, and the whole neighborhood of the Jordan,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were baptized by him in the river Jordan, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when Johnsaw that many of the Pharisees and Sadducees were coming for baptism, he said. "O brood of vipers! Who has warned you to flee from the wrath to come?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Then bring forth fruit worthy of repentance.
B040C003V009	40	3	9	And do not presume to say to yourselves, We have Abraham as our father-I tell you that out of these very stones God is able to raise up descendants for Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	And already the axe is lying at the roots of the trees. Any tree,  therefore, that does not bear good fruit is cut down and cast into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I indeed am baptizing you in water, unto repentance; but One is coming after me, mightier than I, whose sandals I am not worthy to carry. He will baptize you in the Holy Spirit and in fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing-fan is in his hand, and he will thoroughly cleanse the threshing-floor. He will store his wheat in the granary, but will burn up the chaff in unquenchable fire."
B040C003V013	40	3	13	At that very time Jesus was on his way from Galilee to the Jordan,  to John, to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But he tried to prevent him. "It is I," he said, "who need to be baptized by you, and are you coming to me?"
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jesus answered, "Permit it now, for so it is fitting for us to fulfill every religious duty."
B040C003V016	40	3	16	Then he consented. And after Jesus was baptized, as soon as he rose out of the water, lo! the heavens opened, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and alighting upon him,
B040C003V017	40	3	17	while a voice from heaven said, "This is my son, the beloved, In whom I delight."
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led up into the desert by the Spirit, to be tempted by the devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And after he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he became hungry,
B040C004V003	40	4	3	So the tempter came and said to him, "If you are the Son of God, bid these stones to become bread."
B040C004V004	40	4	4	Jesus answered him, "It is written, Not by bread alone shall man live, but by every word that comes from the mouth of God."
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil took him up into the Holy City and stood him on the parapet of the temple,
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to him. "If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down;  for it is written, "He will give his angels charge over thee; Upon their hands they will bear thee up, Lest thou dash thy foot against a stone."
B040C004V007	40	4	7	"It is written again," answered Jesus, "Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God."
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Then the devil took Jesus to a very high mountain, and showed all the kingdoms of the earth and the glory of them,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and said to him, "All these will I give you, if you will fall down and worship me."
B040C004V010	40	4	10	"Begone, Satan!" answered Jesus, "for it is written, "Thou must worship the Lord thy God, and Him only must thou serve."
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil left him, and behold! angels came and began ministering to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now when Jesus heard that Johnhad been arrested, he withdrew into Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	He left Nazareth, and settled in Capernaum-by-the-Lake, near the borders of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	in order that these words spoken through Isaiah the prophet, might be fulfilled.
B040C004V015	40	4	15	Land of Zebulun, land of Naphtali; The road by the Lake; the country beyond Jordan; Galilee of the Gentiles!
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people who were dwelling in darkness Have seen a great light;  And on those who were dwelling in the land of the shadows of death Light has dawned.
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time Jesus began to preach, saying, "Repent for the kingdom of heaven is near."
B040C004V018	40	4	18	And as he was walking by the see of Galilee, he saw two brothers-  Simon who is called Peter, and Andrew, his brother-casting their net into the sea, for they were fishermen.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	"Come, follow me," said Jesus, "And I will make you fishers of men."
B040C004V020	40	4	20	And they dropped their nets at once, and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	As he went farther on he saw two other brothers, Jamesthe son of Zebedee, and Johnhis brother, in the boat with Zebedee their father,  mending their nets, and he called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	They immediately left the boat and their father, and followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	Then Jesus went about through Galilee, teaching in the synagogues,  and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every kind of disease and infirmity among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And his fame spread throughout all Syria. They brought all the sick to him, those who were suffering from various diseases and troubles-  demoniacs, epileptics, paralytics-and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	Great crowds followed him from Galilee, from the ten towns, from Jerusalem, and Judea, and from beyond Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	When he saw the crowds, he went up the mountain, and when he had seated himself, his disciples came to him,
B040C005V002	40	5	2	and opening his lips he began to teach them, saying.
B040C005V003	40	5	3	"Blessed are the poor in spirit, for the kingdom of heaven is theirs.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	"Blessed are those who mourn, for they shall be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	"Blessed are the gentle, for they shall inherit the earth."
B040C005V006	40	5	6	"Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for the righteousness, for they shall be completely satisfied.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	"Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	"Blessed are the pure in heart, for they shall see God.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	"Blessed are the peacemakers, for they shall be called sons of God.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	"Blessed are those who have been persecuted in the cause of righteousness, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	"Blessed are you when they shall revile you, and persecute you, and say all manner of evil against you falsely, for my names sake.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	"Rejoice and exult in it, because your reward was great in the heavens; for so did they persecute the prophets before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	"You are the salt of the earth; but if the salt lose its savor, in what way shall it be salted? It is henceforth good for nothing but to be thrown out and trodden under foot of men.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	"You are the light of the world. A city built on a hilltop cannot be hid;
B040C005V015	40	5	15	"nor do men light a lamp, and put it under the bushel, but on the lamp-stand, and it gives light to all who are in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	"So let your light shine before men that they may see good you do,  and give glory to your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	"Do not suppose that I am come to destroy the Law or the Prophets. I am come not to destroy, but to fulfil.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	"In solemn truth I tell you that until heaven and earth pass away,  not an iota, not a comma, will pass from the Law until all has taken place.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	"So whoever breaks one of these least commandments, and teaches others to break them, will be least in the kingdom of heaven. But he who keeps them and teaches them, he will be called great in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	"For I assure you that unless your righteousness exceed that of the scribes and Pharisees, you will not find entrance into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	"You have heard that it was said to the ancients, "Thou shall not commit murder, and "he who commits murder shall be liable to condemnation by the court;
B040C005V022	40	5	22	but I say to you that he who becomes angry with his brother shall be liable to condemnation by the court; and he who says to his brother Raca, shall be liable to condemnation by the Sanhedrin, while he who curses his brother shall be liable to the Gehenna of Fire.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	"If therefore when you are offering your gift upon the altar, and there remember that your brother has a grievance against you,
B040C005V024	40	5	24	"leave there your gift before the altar, and go and make friends with your brother, first of all; then come and offer your gift.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	"Come to terms with your opponent quickly, while you are yet with him on the way to the court, to prevent your opponent from handing you over to the judge, and the judge to the jailer, and so you be thrown into prison.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	"I tell you truly that you would certainly not get out from there until you had paid back the last cent.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	"You have heard that it was said, "Thou shalt not commit adultery.
B040C005V028	40	5	28	But I say to you that whoever looks with lust at a woman has already committed adultery with her in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	And if your eye, your right eye, entices you to sin, pluck it out and cast it from you. It is better for you to lose one of your bodily organs, than to have your whole body go down into the pit.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if your right hand entices you into sin, cut it off and cast it from you; for it is better for you to lose one of your bodily organs,  than to have your whole body go down into the pit.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	"It was also said, "Whoever divorces his wife must give her a bill of separation.
B040C005V032	40	5	32	But I tell you that anyone who divorces his wife, except on the ground of unchastity, makes her an adulteress, and whoever marries her when so divorced, commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	"Again you have heard that it was said to the men of old, "You must not forswear yourselves, but must perform your vows to the Lord.
B040C005V034	40	5	34	"But I say to you, swear not at all; neither by the sky, for it is Gods throne;
B040C005V035	40	5	35	"nor by the earth, for it is the footstool of his feet; nor by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the Great King.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	"Nor must you swear by your head, since you cannot make one hair white or black.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	"But let your word be simply Yes or No;anything beyond this comes from the Evil One.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	"You have heard that it was said, "An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.
B040C005V039	40	5	39	"But I tell you not to retaliate the injury; but whoever strikes you on the right cheek, turn the other to him also;
B040C005V040	40	5	40	"and if any one wants to go to law with you and takes away your coat, let him take your cloak also.
B040C005V041	40	5	41	"Whoever impresses you to go one mile, go two miles with him.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	"Give to him who asks, and from him who wants to borrow from you, do not turn away.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	"You have heard that it was said, "You shall love your neighbor and hate your enemy."
B040C005V044	40	5	44	"But I say to you, love your enemies, and pray for those who persecute you.
B040C005V045	40	5	45	"So you will become sons of your heavenly Father; for he makes his sun to rise upon sinners as well as saints, and sends rain upon the unjust and the just.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	"For if you love only those who love you, what reward have you?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	"Even the tax-gatherers do that, do they not? And if you show courtesy to your brother only, what are you doing more than others?  Even the Gentiles do that, do they not?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	"You then must be perfect, as your heavenly Father is perfect."
B040C006V001	40	6	1	"Be careful not to do your good deeds in the sight of men, in order to be observed by them. If you do, you have no reward with your heavenly Father.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	"And whatever you give alms, do not sound a trumpet before you as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and streets, in order that men may praise them. In solemn truth I tell you they already have their reward in full.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	"But when you give alms, do not let your right hand know what your left is doing,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	"so that your alms may be in secret; and your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	"And whenever you pray, do not be like the hypocrites. For they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and on the corners of the avenues, in order that men may see them. In solemn truth I tell you that they have their reward in full.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	"But you, when you pray, go into your own room and shut your door;  pray to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	"While praying do not say the same words over and over again, as the Gentiles do, for they suppose that by their much speaking they will gain attention.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	"Do not be like them, for your Father knows what you need before you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	"So pray in this way. "Our Father who art in heaven, May thy name be hallowed,
B040C006V010	40	6	10	thy kingdom come, and thy will be done, On earth, as in heaven.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give us today our bread for the day before us;
B040C006V012	40	6	12	And forgive us our debts as we also have forgiven our debtors;
B040C006V013	40	6	13	And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the Evil One;  For thine is the kingdom and the power and the glory. Amen.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	"For if you forgive men their offenses against you, your heavenly Father will forgive you also;
B040C006V015	40	6	15	"but if you do not forgive men your offenses, neither will your heavenly Father forgive you your offenses.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	"When you fast, do not look downcast like the hypocrites; for they disfigure their faces so that it may be apparent to men that they are fasting. In solemn truth I tell you, they already have received their reward.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	"But when one of you fasts, let him anoint his head and wash his face,
B040C006V018	40	6	18	"so that he may not appear to men to be fasting, but to his Father who is in secret; and his Father who sees in secret will reward him.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	"Store up for yourselves no treasures on earth, where moth and rust consume, and where thieves break through and steal;
B040C006V020	40	6	20	"but store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust consume, and where thieves do not break through nor steal.
B040C006V021	40	6	21	"For wherever your treasure is, there will your heart be also.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	"The lamp of the body is the eye. Therefore if your eye is sound,  your whole body will be well lighted;
B040C006V023	40	6	23	"but if your eye is unsound, your whole body will be darkened. If then the very light within you is darkness, how dense is that darkness!
B040C006V024	40	6	24	"No slave can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will pay heed to the one and despise the other.  You cannot be the slaves both of God and of gold.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	"For this reason I say to you, do not be anxious about your life,  inquiring what you shall eat or what you shall drink, nor yet for your body, inquiring what you shall wear. Is not your life more than its food, and your body than its clothing?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	"Behold! the birds in the sky! They neither sow, nor reap, nor gather into barns, yet your heavenly Father feeds them; and are not you worth more than they?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	"Which one of you by being anxious is able to add even one cubit to his stature?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	"Why be anxious then about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow. They toil not, neither do they spin.
B040C006V029	40	6	29	"But I say to you that not even Solomon in all his glory was robed like one of these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	"If God then so clothes the grass of the field, which blooms today,  and tomorrow is cast into the oven, will he not much more clothe you,  you of little faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	"Then do not be anxious,saying, What shall we eat? or What shall we drink? or What shall we wear?"
B040C006V032	40	6	32	"For all these are things that the Gentiles are eagerly seeking; for your heavenly Father knows that you have need of them all.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	"But continue to seek first his kingdom and his righteousness, and all these things shall be added to you.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	"Do not then be anxious about tomorrow, for tomorrow will bring its own anxieties. Enough for each day are its own troubles."
B040C007V001	40	7	1	"Judge not, that you may be judged, yourselves;
B040C007V002	40	7	2	"for with what judgment you judge, you will be judged, and in what measure you measure, others will measure to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	"And why do you look at the mote in your brothers eye, and fail to notice the beam which is in your own eye?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	"Or how will you say to your brother, Permit me to remove the mote from your eye, when, behold, the beam is in your own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	"Hypocrite! First cast out the beam from your own eye, and then you will see clearly how to cast the mote out of your brothers eye.
B040C007V006	40	7	6	"Do not give what is holy to the dogs, nor cast your pearls before swine; lest in turn they trample them under their feet, and then turn and attack you.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	"Ask, and it will be given you; seek, and you will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you.
