B040C022V018	40	22	18	And Jesus, because he knew their malice, said.
B040C022V019	40	22	19	"Hypocrites! Why are you tempting me? Show me the tribute money." So they brought him a shilling.
B040C022V020	40	22	20	"Whose likeness and inscription is this?" he asked.
B040C022V021	40	22	21	"Caesars," they answered. Then he said to them, "Render unto Caesar the things that are Caesars, and unto God the things that are Gods."
B040C022V022	40	22	22	When they heard this they were astonished, and left him and went away.
B040C022V023	40	22	23	That very day there came to him some Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection. and they questioned him.
B040C022V024	40	22	24	"Master," they said, "Moses taught that if a man dies without issue,  his brother is to marry the widow, and raise up a family for his brother.
B040C022V025	40	22	25	"Now there were of our number seven brothers; and the first married and died. As he had no children, he left his wife to his brother;
B040C022V026	40	22	26	"In the same way the second also died, and the third, unto the seventh.
B040C022V027	40	22	27	"Last of all the woman died.
B040C022V028	40	22	28	"In the resurrection, then, whose wife will she be? They all had her."
B040C022V029	40	22	29	In answer Jesus said. "You err because you do not know the Scriptures, nor the power of God.
B040C022V030	40	22	30	"For in the resurrection men do not marry, nor are women given in marriage, but they are like angels in heaven.
B040C022V031	40	22	31	"But concerning the resurrection of the dead, did you never read what was spoken to you by God,
B040C022V032	40	22	32	"I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living."
B040C022V033	40	22	33	And when the crowds heard it, they were astonished at his teaching.
B040C022V034	40	22	34	As soon as the Pharisees heard that Jesus had silenced the Sadducees, they gathered themselves together,
B040C022V035	40	22	35	and one of them, a lawyer, tested him by asking a question.
B040C022V036	40	22	36	"Master, which is the great commandment in the law?"
B040C022V037	40	22	37	Jesus answered, "Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind.
B040C022V038	40	22	38	"This is the great and first commandment.
B040C022V039	40	22	39	"The second, which is like it, is this, "Thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself.
B040C022V040	40	22	40	"On those two commandments hang the whole law and the prophets."
B040C022V041	40	22	41	Now while the Pharisees were together, Jesus put this question to them.
B040C022V042	40	22	42	"What is your opinion concerning the Christ? Whose Son is he?"  "Davids," they answered.
B040C022V043	40	22	43	"How then, "he said, "does David in the Spirit call him Lord, saying,
B040C022V044	40	22	44	"The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand Until I put thine enemies beneath thy feet?
B040C022V045	40	22	45	"If David calls him Lord, how can he be his Son?"
B040C022V046	40	22	46	No one could answer him a word, nor did any one dare from that day to ask him another question.
B040C023V001	40	23	1	Then said Jesus to the crowds and to his disciples.
B040C023V002	40	23	2	"The Scribes and Pharisees sit in Moses seat;
B040C023V003	40	23	3	"therefore do and observe whatever they bid you; but do not do as they do, for they preach, but do not practise.
B040C023V004	40	23	4	"For they bind heavy burdens and lay them on mens shoulders, but they themselves will not lift a finger to move them.
B040C023V005	40	23	5	"For they do all their good deeds to be gazed on of men. They widen their phylacteries,
B040C023V006	40	23	6	"and lengthen the tassels, and are fond of the best places at banquets, and the front seats in the synagogues.
B040C023V007	40	23	7	"They enjoy salutations in the market-places, and to have men call them Rabbi.
B040C023V008	40	23	8	"But you are not to be called Rabbi;for one is your Teacher, and you are all brothers;
B040C023V009	40	23	9	"and call no one Father on earth, for One is your Father in heaven.
B040C023V010	40	23	10	"And call no one Leader, because One is your leader, even the Christ.
B040C023V011	40	23	11	"Whoever is great among you shall be your minister;
B040C023V012	40	23	12	"whoever exalts himself shall be humbled, and he who humbles himself shall be exalted.
B040C023V013	40	23	13	"But woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! You shut the kingdom of heaven in mens faces; for you do not enter, yourselves,  nor do you permit those who are about to come in, to enter.
B040C023V014	40	23	14	(Is wanting in the oldest manuscripts.)
B040C023V015	40	23	15	"Woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you scour sea and land to make one proselyte, and when he is gained, you make him twofold more a son of hell than you are, yourselves.
B040C023V016	40	23	16	"Woe unto you, blind guides, who say, If any one swears by the Sanctuary, it is nothing, but if any one swears by the gold of the Sanctuary, the oath is binding.
B040C023V017	40	23	17	"You fools and blind; for which is greater, the gold, or the Sanctuary which hallows the gold?
B040C023V018	40	23	18	"You say, too, that whoever swears by the offering that is upon it,  his oath is binding.
B040C023V019	40	23	19	"You blind! Which is greater, the offering or the altar which hallows the offering?
B040C023V020	40	23	20	"He then, who swears by the altar, swears by it and by everything on it;
B040C023V021	40	23	21	"and he who swears by the Sanctuary swears by it and by Him who dwells therein;
B040C023V022	40	23	22	"and he who swears by heaven, swears by the throne of God and by Him who sits thereon.
B040C023V023	40	23	23	"Woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you tithe mint and anise and cummin, and neglect the weightier matters of the Law -  justice and mercy and good faith; these latter you ought to have done, and not to have left the former undone.
B040C023V024	40	23	24	"You blind guides! who strain out the gnat and swallow the camel!
B040C023V025	40	23	25	"Woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you clean the outside of the cup and the plate, but within they are filled with extortion and excess.
B040C023V026	40	23	26	"You blind Pharisees, first clean the inside of the cup and of the plate, so that the outside of it may be clean also.
B040C023V027	40	23	27	"Woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! You are like white-  washed sepulchers. They look beautiful without, but within they are filled with dead mens bones and all rottenness.
B040C023V028	40	23	28	"Just so you also outwardly appear to men, just, but within you are full of hypocrisy and wickedness.
B040C023V029	40	23	29	"Woe unto you, Scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! You rebuild the tombs of the prophets, and adorn the monuments of the righteous, and say,
B040C023V030	40	23	30	"If we had lived in the days of our fathers, we would not have been their comrades in the murder of the prophets.
B040C023V031	40	23	31	"So you bear witness against yourselves, that you are the descendants of those who slew the prophets!
B040C023V032	40	23	32	"Fill up then the measure of your fathers!
B040C023V033	40	23	33	"You serpents! You vipers brood! How shall you escape the judgment of hell?
B040C023V034	40	23	34	"For this cause, behold! I am sending you prophets and wise men and scribes. Some of them you will kill and crucify; some of them you will scourge in your synagogues, and pursue from city to city;
B040C023V035	40	23	35	"that upon your heads may come every drop of innocent blood spilt upon the earth, from the blood of Abel, the just, to the blood of Zechariah the son of Berechiah, whom you murdered between the Sanctuary and the altar.
B040C023V036	40	23	36	"In solemn truth I tell you that all these things will come upon this generation.
B040C023V037	40	23	37	"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, murdering the prophets, and stoning those who have been sent to you! How often would I have gathered your children together, as a hen gathers her chickens under her wings, and you would not!
B040C023V038	40	23	38	"Behold, your house is left to you desolate!
B040C023V039	40	23	39	"For I tell you that never shall you see me again until you say,  "Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord." "nor did they know until the deluge came and swept them away; so will be the coming of the Son of man.
B040C024V001	40	24	1	Then Jesus left the Temple courts and was walking away, when his disciples came to point out to him the Temple buildings.
B040C024V002	40	24	2	"You see all these buildings?" he answered them; "I tell you solemnly that there shall not be left here one stone upon another,  that shall not be torn down."
B040C024V003	40	24	3	When he had seated himself on the Mount of Olives, his disciples came to him privately, saying, "Tell us, when will these things happen, and what will be the sign of your coming, and of the end of the age?"
B040C024V004	40	24	4	"Take care," Jesus answered, "that no one mislead you;
B040C024V005	40	24	5	"for many will come in my name saying, I am the Christ, and will mislead many.
B040C024V006	40	24	6	"And you will hear of wars and rumors of wars; see to it that you are not afraid. Such things must happen, but the end is not yet.
B040C024V007	40	24	7	"Such things must happen, nation, and kingdom against kingdom, and there will be famines and earthquakes in various places.
B040C024V008	40	24	8	"All these things are the beginning of birth-pangs.
B040C024V009	40	24	9	"Then they will deliver you up to suffer affliction, and will put you to death, and you will be hated by all nations for my names sake.
B040C024V010	40	24	10	"And then many will stumble and fall, and will betray one another,  and hate one another.
B040C024V011	40	24	11	"Many false prophets will rise up and mislead many;
B040C024V012	40	24	12	"and because of the increase of iniquity the love of the majority will grow cold;
B040C024V013	40	24	13	"but he who endures to the end will be saved.
B040C024V014	40	24	14	"And this gospel of the kingdom shall be proclaimed throughout the whole inhabited earth, for a testimony to the Gentiles, and then will come the end.
B040C024V015	40	24	15	"So when you see the Abomination of Desolation spoken of by the prophet Daniel, standing in the holy place let the reader take note of this,
B040C024V016	40	24	16	"then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains;
B040C024V017	40	24	17	"let him who is upon the housetop not go down to get the things in his house,
B040C024V018	40	24	18	"and the man in the field not turn back to get his cloak.
B040C024V019	40	24	19	"Alas for thee women who are with child, and for the nursing mothers in those days!
B040C024V020	40	24	20	"But pray that your flight may not be in the winter; nor on a Sabbath;
B040C024V021	40	24	21	"for then shall be a time of great tribulation, such as has not been from the beginning of the world until now, no, and never shall be again.
B040C024V022	40	24	22	"And if these days had not been shortened, no flesh would have been saved; but for the elects sake these days will be cut short.
B040C024V023	40	24	23	"If at that time any one should say to you, See, here is the Christ! or There he is! believe him not.
B040C024V024	40	24	24	"For false christs and false prophets will arise, and will work great signs and wonders, so as to mislead, if it were possible, the very elect.
B040C024V025	40	24	25	"See, I have forewarned you! So if they say to you,
B040C024V026	40	24	26	"See, He is in the desert, do not go out there. "See, He is in the inner room, do not believe it.
B040C024V027	40	24	27	"For just as the lightning flashes from the east, and is seen even to the west; so will be the coming of the Son of man.
B040C024V028	40	24	28	"Wherever the corpse lies, there will the vultures flock together.
B040C024V029	40	24	29	"But immediately after the tribulation of those days, "The sun will be darkened, The moon will not shed her light, The stars will fall from the sky, And the powers of the heavens will be shaken.
B040C024V030	40	24	30	"Then the signs of the Son of man will appear in the sky; and then all the tribes of the earth will lament, when they see the Son of man coming upon the clouds of heaven, with power and great glory.
B040C024V031	40	24	31	"And he will send forth his angels with a great sound of a trumpet,  and they will gather his elect together from the four winds, from utmost heaven to utmost earth.
B040C024V032	40	24	32	"Learn from the fig tree, her parable; when her branches are become soft, and put forth leaves, you know that summer is near;
B040C024V033	40	24	33	"so you also, when you see these signs, know that He is near, at the very doors.
B040C024V034	40	24	34	"I tell you in solemn truth, that the present generation shall not pass away till all these things happen.
B040C024V035	40	24	35	"Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.
B040C024V036	40	24	36	"But no one knows about that day and hour, not even the angels in heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.
B040C024V037	40	24	37	"And as were the days of Noah, so will be the coming of the Son of man.
B040C024V038	40	24	38	"For just as in the days before the deluge they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the very day when Noah entered the ark,
B040C024V040	40	24	40	"At that time there will be two men in the field; one will be taken,  and one will be left.
B040C024V041	40	24	41	"Two women will be grinding at the mill; one will be taken and the other left.
B040C024V042	40	24	42	"Keep guard then, for you do not know the day on which your Master is coming.
B040C024V043	40	24	43	"But know this, that if the master of the house had known in what watch the thief was coming, he would have been on his guard, and would not have allowed his house to be broken into.
B040C024V044	40	24	44	"Therefore you also must be ready, for in an hour when you do not expect him, the Son of man is coming.
B040C024V045	40	24	45	"Who, then, is the faithful and prudent slave, to whom his master has entrusted his household, to give them their food in due season?
B040C024V046	40	24	46	"Blessed is that slave whom his Master, when he comes, shall find so doing.
B040C024V047	40	24	47	"In solemn truth I tell you that he will set him over all his property.
B040C024V048	40	24	48	"But if, because he is a bad slave, he should say to himself, My Master is a long time in coming,
B040C024V049	40	24	49	"and if he begins to beat his fellow slaves, and to eat or drink with the drunkards,
B040C024V050	40	24	50	"on a day when he is not expecting him, and at an hour which he does not know, the Master of that servant will arrive
B040C024V051	40	24	51	"and will scourge him severely, and allot him a place among hypocrites, where will be weeping and gnashing of teeth."
B040C025V001	40	25	1	"Then will the kingdom of heaven be likened to ten maidens who took their lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom and the bride.
B040C025V002	40	25	2	"And five of them were foolish, and five were wise.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	"The foolish took their lamps, but took no oil with them;
B040C025V004	40	25	4	"but the wise took oil in their flasks with their lamps.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	"Now because the bridegroom tarried, they all fell to nodding and went on sleeping.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	"But at midnight there arose a cry, "Behold, the bridegroom! Go out to meet him!
B040C025V007	40	25	7	"Then all those maidens rose and trimmed their lamps;
B040C025V008	40	25	8	"and the foolish said to the wise, "Give us some of your oil, for our lamps are going out.
B040C025V009	40	25	9	"Not so, answered the wise, for there may not be enough for you and for us. Go to the shops, rather, and buy some for yourselves.
B040C025V010	40	25	10	"And while they were going away to buy, the bridegroom came; and those who were ready went in with him to the wedding-feast. And the door was shut.
B040C025V011	40	25	11	"Afterwards the other maidens came and cried, "Lord, Lord, open unto us!
B040C025V012	40	25	12	"In solemn truth I tell you, he replied, I know you not.
B040C025V013	40	25	13	"Be watchful then, for you know neither the day nor the hour.
B040C025V014	40	25	14	"For it is like a man going into another country, who summoned his slaves, and committed his property to their care.
B040C025V015	40	25	15	"To one he gave five talents, to another two, and to another, one -  to each according to his individual ability - and then set out on his travels.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	"At once the man who had received the five talents went out and traded with them, and made five talents more.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	"In the same way the one who got two talents made another two.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	"But he who had received the one talent went off, and dug a hole in the ground, and hid his masters money.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	"After a long time the master of those slaves came, and demanded a reckoning with them.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	"The man who had received the five talents came, bringing five more,  and said. "Master, five talents you entrusted to me; see, I have gained five more.
B040C025V021	40	25	21	"Well done, good and faithful slave, replied his master; You have been faithful over many things. Enter into your masters joy.
B040C025V022	40	25	22	"The second, who had received the two talents, came up and said.  "Master, it was two talents that you entrusted to me; see, I have gained two more.
B040C025V023	40	25	23	"Well done, good and faithful slave, his master replied, You have been faithful over many things; enter into your masters joy.
B040C025V024	40	25	24	"Then the man who had received the one talent came up and said.  "Master, I knew you were a hard man, reaping where you had not sown,  and gathering where you had not scattered;
B040C025V025	40	25	25	"so I was afraid; I went away and buried your talent in the earth.  There, you have what belongs to you!
B040C025V026	40	25	26	"You wicked and lazy slave, said his master. You say you knew that I reap where I have not sowed, and gather where I have not scattered?
B040C025V027	40	25	27	"Then you ought to have deposited my money with the bankers, and at my coming I should have received back my property with interest.
B040C025V028	40	25	28	"So take away the talent from him, and give it to the man who has ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	"(For to every one who has, it shall be given, and he shall have abundance; but from him who has not shall be taken away even what he has.)
B040C025V030	40	25	30	"But cast out the worthless slave into the outer darkness; there will be the weeping and the gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V031	40	25	31	"But when the Son of man comes in his glory, and all the angels with him, then will he take his seat on the throne of his glory;
B040C025V032	40	25	32	"and all the nations will be gathered in his presence. And he will separate them one from another, as a shepherd divides his sheep from the goats;
B040C025V033	40	25	33	"and he will place the sheep on his right hand, and the goats on his left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	"Then he, the King will say to those on his right hand. "Come, my Fathers blessed ones, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.
B040C025V035	40	25	35	"For I was hungry, and you gave me food; I was thirsty, and you gave me drink; I was a stranger, and you took me in;
B040C025V036	40	25	36	"I was naked, and you clothed me; I was sick, and you visited me; I was in prison, and you came to see me.
B040C025V037	40	25	37	"Then shall the righteous answer him, saying. Master, when did we see you hungry and feed you; or thirsty and give you drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	"When did we see you a stranger and take you in; or naked and clothe you?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	"When did we see you sick or in prison, and come to see you?
B040C025V040	40	25	40	"In solemn truth I tell you, the King will answer them, that inasmuch as you have done it unto one of the least of these, my brothers, you have done it unto me.
B040C025V041	40	25	41	"Then he will say to those also at his left hand. Depart from me,  accursed ones, into the eternal fire prepared for the devil and his angels;
B040C025V042	40	25	42	"for I was hungry, and you gave me no food; I was thirsty, and you gave me no drink;
B040C025V043	40	25	43	"I was a stranger, and you took me not in; naked, and you clothed me not; sick, or in prison, and you visited me not.
B040C025V044	40	25	44	"Then will they also answer, Master, when did we ever see you hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison,  and did not minister to you?
B040C025V045	40	25	45	"But he will reply, In solemn truth I tell you that inasmuch as you did not do it unto one of these least, you did not do it unto me.
B040C025V046	40	25	46	"And these will go away into eternal punishment; but the righteous into eternal life."
B040C026V001	40	26	1	Now it happened that after Jesus had finished all these discourses,  he said to his disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	"You know that the Passover is coming in two days, and the Son of man will be delivered up to be crucified."
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then the chief priests and the elders of the people met together in the court of the palace of the high priest who was called Caiaphas,
B040C026V004	40	26	4	and they plotted together to get Jesus into their power by a trick,  and to put him to death;
B040C026V005	40	26	5	but said they, "Not during the feast, for fear of causing a riot among the people."
B040C026V006	40	26	6	While Jesus was staying in Bethany, in the house of Simon the Leper,
B040C026V007	40	26	7	a woman came up to him who had an alabaster vase of very costly perfume, and poured it over his head, as he reclined at table.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	when the disciples saw it, they were indignant, and exclaimed.
B040C026V009	40	26	9	"Why is this waste? This perfume could have been sold for a good sum, and the money given to the poor."
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But when Jesus understood it he said to them. "Why are you annoying the woman? This is a beautiful deed she has done for me;
B040C026V011	40	26	11	"for the poor you have with you always, but me you will not always have.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	"In pouring this perfume on my body, she was preparing me for my burial.
B040C026V013	40	26	13	"In solemn truth I tell you that wherever this gospel shall be preached in the whole world, what she has done shall be told about,  as her memorial."
B040C026V014	40	26	14	It was then that one of the Twelve, he who was called Judas Iscariot,
B040C026V015	40	26	15	went to the chief priests and said, "What are you ready to give me for betraying him to you?" So they weighed him thirty pieces of silver;
B040C026V016	40	26	16	and from that time he kept looking for a chance to betray him.
B040C026V017	40	26	17	On the first day of the feast of Unleavened Bread, the disciples came to Jesus and said, "Where do you want us to make preparation for you eat the Passover?"
B040C026V018	40	26	18	"Go into the city," he answered, "to a certain man, and tell him.  "The Teacher says. "My time is near. I am going to keep the Passover at your house, with my disciples.""
B040C026V019	40	26	19	The disciples did as Jesus told them, and made ready the Passover.
B040C026V020	40	26	20	When evening came he reclined at table with the Twelve;
B040C026V021	40	26	21	and as they were eating, he said to them, "In solemn truth I tell you that one of you is going to betray me!"
B040C026V022	40	26	22	In deep distress they began to ask him, each in turn, "It is not I,  is it, Master?"
B040C026V023	40	26	23	In reply he said. "One who has dipped his hand with me in the dish will betray me.
B040C026V024	40	26	24	"The Son of man is indeed to go as it is written concerning him, but woe to that man by whom the Son of man shall be betrayed. It were good for that man if he had never been born."
B040C026V025	40	26	25	In answer, Judas, who betrayed him, said, "Surely it is not I,  Rabbi?" He said to him, "Is it not?"
B040C026V026	40	26	26	And as they were eating, Jesus took bread and, when he had blessed it, he broke it and gave to his disciples, saying, "Take, eat, this is my body."
B040C026V027	40	26	27	And when he had taken the cup and given thanks, he gave it to them,  saying.
B040C026V028	40	26	28	"Drink from it, all of you; for this is my blood of the Covenant,  which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins.
B040C026V029	40	26	29	"But I say to you, I will never again drink of this fruit of the vine, until that day when I drink it new with you in the kingdom of my Father."
B040C026V030	40	26	30	So after singing a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.
B040C026V031	40	26	31	Then Jesus said to them. "This very night even you will all stumble and fall away from me; for it is written, "I will smite the shepherd,  and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.
B040C026V032	40	26	32	But after I am raised up I will go before you into Galilee."
B040C026V033	40	26	33	"If they all stumble and fall away from you," answered Peter, "I will never do so!"
B040C026V034	40	26	34	Jesus said to him, "In solemn truth I tell you that on this very night, before cockcrow, you will deny me three times!"
B040C026V035	40	26	35	But Peter said to him, "Even if I must die with you, I will never deny you." And so said all the disciples.
B040C026V036	40	26	36	Then Jesus went with them to a place called Gethsemane, and said to his disciples, "Sit down here, while I go and pray yonder."
B040C026V037	40	26	37	And he took Peter and the two sons of Zebedee with him, and began to be in anguish and sore distress,
B040C026V038	40	26	38	and he said to them. "My soul is an anguish, even unto death! Stay here, and keep watch with me."
B040C026V039	40	26	39	Then he went forward a short distance, and fell on his face and prayed. "O, my Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from me;  nevertheless, not as I will, but as thou wit."
B040C026V040	40	26	40	Then he came to his disciples, and found them asleep, and said to Peter. "So you were none of you strong enough to watch with me even one hour!
B040C026V041	40	26	41	"Watch and pray that you may not enter into temptation. The spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak."
B040C026V042	40	26	42	Then he went away again a second time and prayed, saying, "O, my Father, if this cup cannot pass except I drink it, Thy will be done."
B040C026V043	40	26	43	He came again and found them sleeping, for their eyes were heavy.
B040C026V044	40	26	44	So he left them and went away again, and prayed the third time in the same words as before.
B040C026V045	40	26	45	Then he came to the disciples and said. "Sleep on now, and take your rest. Look! the hour is at hand; the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of wicked men.
B040C026V046	40	26	46	"Rouse yourselves! Let us go. My betrayer is close at hand!"
B040C026V047	40	26	47	Barely had he spoken these words when Judas, one of the Twelve,  appeared, accompanied by a great crowd of men with swords and staves,  from the chief priests and elders of the people.
B040C026V048	40	26	48	Now his betrayer had given them a sign, saying. "Whoever I kiss is the man; arrest him."
B040C026V049	40	26	49	So he came straight up to Jesus and said, "Hail, Rabbi!" and kissed him eagerly.
B040C026V050	40	26	50	"Friend, do that for which you came," said Jesus. Then they came forward and laid hands on Jesus, and arrested him.
B040C026V051	40	26	51	And, behold, one of these who were with Jesus stretched out his hand and drew his sword, and smote the slave of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
B040C026V052	40	26	52	Then Jesus said to him. "Put back your sword into its place! for all who take the sword will perish by the sword.
B040C026V053	40	26	53	"Do you not suppose that I am able to appeal to my Father to furnish me at this very moment with twelve legions of angels?
B040C026V054	40	26	54	"But if I did, how could the Scriptures be fulfilled that say that thus it must happen?"
B040C026V055	40	26	55	Then Jesus said to the crowds. "Are you come out as against a robber, with swords and staves to arrest me? Day after day, I sat in the temple courts teaching, and you did not apprehend me.
B040C026V056	40	26	56	"But all this has happened in order that the Scriptures might be fulfilled."
B040C026V057	40	26	57	Then all his disciples forsook him and fled; but those who had apprehended Jesus led him away to Caiaphas, the high priest, where the scribes and the elders had assembled.
B040C026V058	40	26	58	Now Peter was following him, afar off, as far as the courtyard of the high priest; and when he got in, he was sitting with the officers, to see the end.
B040C026V059	40	26	59	And the chief priests and the whole Sanhedrin were trying to get false evidence against Jesus, in order that they might have him executed;
B040C026V060	40	26	60	but they found none, although many false witnesses came forward.
B040C026V061	40	26	61	However, at last two came forward who said, "This fellow declared,  I can destroy the Temple of God and build it in three days."
B040C026V062	40	26	62	Rising to his feet the high priest asked Jesus. "Do you make no answer? What is it that these are testifying against you?"
B040C026V063	40	26	63	But Jesus kept silence. Again the high priest addressed him, "I adjure you by the Living God, tell us if you are the Christ, the Son of God!"
B040C026V064	40	26	64	"I am He," Jesus answered; "yet I tell you that from this time on you will see the Son of man sitting at the right hand of Power, and coming upon the clouds of heaven."
B040C026V065	40	26	65	Then the high priest tore his garments, saying. "He has spoken blasphemy! What further need have we of witnesses? For behold, now you have heard his blasphemy!
B040C026V066	40	26	66	"What is your verdict?" "He ought to die," they answered.
B040C026V067	40	26	67	Then did they spit in his face, and buffeted him; and some struck him with the palms of their hands, and cried.
B040C026V068	40	26	68	"Prophesy to us, you Christ! Who is it who struck you?"
B040C026V069	40	26	69	Now Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard, and one of the maidservants came up to him and said, "You also were with Jesus, the Galilean!"
B040C026V070	40	26	70	But he denied it before them all; "I do not know what you mean," he said.
B040C026V071	40	26	71	Soon afterward he went out into the porch, and another maid saw him,  and said to those who were there, "This fellow certainly was with Jesus, the Nazarene!"
B040C026V072	40	26	72	And again he denied it with an oath, saying, "I never knew the man."
B040C026V073	40	26	73	A little later the bystanders came up and said to Peter, "You also are certainly one of them, for your speech betrays you."
B040C026V074	40	26	74	Then he began to curse and swear, saying, "I never knew the man."  Immediately the cock crew!
B040C026V075	40	26	75	Then Peter recalled the word that Jesus had spoken, "Before the cock crow, you shall three times deny me" - and he went out and broke out into bitter weeping.
B040C027V001	40	27	1	And when the morning came, all the chief priests and the elders of the people took counsel against Jesus, how they might put him to death.
B040C027V002	40	27	2	After they had bound him, they led him away, and handed him over to Pilate, the Roman Governor.
B040C027V003	40	27	3	Then when Judas, his betrayer, saw that he was condemned, he repented and brought back the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders.
B040C027V004	40	27	4	"I have sinned," he said, "in betraying innocent blood!" "What is that to us?" they answered; "you must see to that."
B040C027V005	40	27	5	And flinging down the silver into the Sanctuary, he rushed out, and went and hanged himself.
B040C027V006	40	27	6	The chief priests took the money, and said, "It would be wrong to put it into the temple-treasury, because it is the price of blood."
B040C027V007	40	27	7	So after the consultation they bought the Potters Field with it,  for a burial-place for strangers.
B040C027V008	40	27	8	That is the reason why, to this day, the field is called "The Field of Blood."
B040C027V009	40	27	9	Then was fulfilled the word spoken by the prophet Jeremiah. And I took the thirty pieces of silver, the price of him who had been priced, whom certain of the Children of Israel had priced;
B040C027V010	40	27	10	and gave them for the Potters Field, as the Lord had appointed me.
B040C027V011	40	27	11	Now Jesus stood before the Governor, and the Governor questioned him. "Are you the King of the Jews?" he asked.
B040C027V012	40	27	12	"it is as you say," answered Jesus; but while he was being accused by the chief priests and elders, he answered nothing.
B040C027V013	40	27	13	Then Pilate said to him, "Do you not hear what they are testifying against you?"
B040C027V014	40	27	14	But he made no answer, not even to one charge; insomuch that the Governor was greatly astonished.
B040C027V015	40	27	15	Now it was the Governors custom, during the Passover, to release to the people any one prisoner whom they selected.
B040C027V016	40	27	16	At that time they had a notorious prisoner named Barabbas.
B040C027V017	40	27	17	So when they had assembled, Pilate said to them, "Whom do you want me to release to you, Barabbas, or Jesus who is called Christ?"
B040C027V018	40	27	18	He knew well that it was because of enmity that they had brought Jesus before him.
B040C027V019	40	27	19	And while he was seated upon the judgment-seat, his wife had sent to him, saying, "Have nothing to do with that innocent man, for I have suffered many things today, in a dream, because of him."
B040C027V020	40	27	20	But the chief priests and the elders urged the crowds to ask for Barabbas, and to destroy Jesus.
B040C027V021	40	27	21	So when Pilate said to them, "Which of the two do you want me to release unto you?" they said, "Barabbas."
B040C027V022	40	27	22	And Pilate asked, "What then shall I do with Jesus, who is called Christ?" What one voice they shouted, "Let him be crucified!"
B040C027V023	40	27	23	But Pilate said, "Why, what evil has he done?" But they kept shouting the more fiercely, "Let him be crucified!"
B040C027V024	40	27	24	So when Pilate saw that he was accomplishing nothing, but that on the contrary a riot was threatening, he took water and washed his hands in the presence of the crowd, saying. "I am innocent of the blood of this man; you must answer for it."
B040C027V025	40	27	25	All the people answered, "His blood be upon us and upon our children."
B040C027V026	40	27	26	Then he released Barabbas to them, but Jesus he scourged, and delivered to be crucified.
B040C027V027	40	27	27	Then the soldiers of the Governor took Jesus into the Praetorium,  and gathered all the battalion together.
B040C027V028	40	27	28	They stripped him and put on him a scarlet robe.
B040C027V029	40	27	29	And they twisted a thorny crown for him, and put it on his head, and placed a reed in his right hand. Then they knelt before him, in mockery, crying, "Hail, King of the Jews!"
B040C027V030	40	27	30	And they spit upon him, and took the reed and struck him on the head, again and again.
B040C027V031	40	27	31	At last, when they had finished their mocking, they took the robe off, and put his own garments on him, and led him away to crucify him.
B040C027V032	40	27	32	And as they went out they found a man of Cyrene, Simon by name, whom they compelled to go with them to carry his cross.
B040C027V033	40	27	33	And when they came to a place called Golgotha (the word means "Place of a Skull"),
B040C027V034	40	27	34	they gave Jesus wine to drink, mingled with gall. But after tasting it he refused to drink it.
B040C027V035	40	27	35	After crucifying him, they parted his garments among them by casting lots.
B040C027V036	40	27	36	Then they sat and watched him there.
B040C027V037	40	27	37	They also placed above his head his accusation written, This is Jesus The King of the Jews
B040C027V038	40	27	38	At that time two robbers, also, were crucified with him; one on his right hand, the other on his left.
B040C027V039	40	27	39	Those who passed by reviled him, wagging their heads saying.
B040C027V040	40	27	40	"You who were going to destroy the Temple and build it in three days, save yourself! If you are the Son of God, come down from the cross!"
B040C027V041	40	27	41	In like manner the chief priests, too, with the Scribes and elders,  kept taunting him.
B040C027V042	40	27	42	"He saved other," they said, "himself he cannot save. He, the King of Israel! Let him now come down from the cross, and we will believe on him!
B040C027V043	40	27	43	He put his trust in God. let Him deliver him now, if He cares for him. For he said, I am the Son of God!"
B040C027V044	40	27	44	In the same way the robbers also who were being crucified with him,  dept reviling him.
B040C027V045	40	27	45	Now from noon darkness fell upon the whole land, until three oclock in the afternoon.
B040C027V046	40	27	46	But at three oclock Jesus cried out in loud voice, "Eli, Eli, Lama Sabachthani?" (That is to say, "My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?")
B040C027V047	40	27	47	When they heard this, some of the bystanders said "He is calling for Elijah!"
B040C027V048	40	27	48	At once, one of them ran, and took a sponge, and filling it with vinegar, put it on a reed, and gave him to drink.
B040C027V049	40	27	49	But the rest said. "Let be! Let us see whether Elijah is coming to save him!"
B040C027V050	40	27	50	And Jesus cried again with a loud voice, and yielded up his spirit.
B040C027V051	40	27	51	And lo, the veil of the sanctuary was torn in two, from the top to the bottom;
B040C027V052	40	27	52	the earth quaked; the rocks split; the tombs were opened, and many bodies of the saints who had fallen asleep were raised.
B040C027V053	40	27	53	And coming forth out of the tombs, after his resurrection, they went into the holy city and appeared to many.
B040C027V054	40	27	54	When the Roman captain and the soldiers who were with him, guarding Jesus, saw the earthquake and all that happened, they were greatly terrified and said, "Certainly this man must have been Gods Son."
B040C027V055	40	27	55	And there were present several women who were looking on from a distance; they had followed Jesus from a Galilee, ministering to him.
B040C027V056	40	27	56	among them being Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of Jamesand Joses,  and the mother of Zebedees sons.
B040C027V057	40	27	57	When it was eventide, there came a rich man of Arimathea, named Josephus, who was himself a disciple of Jesus.
B040C027V058	40	27	58	This man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B040C027V059	40	27	59	Pilate then commanded that it be given over to him.
B040C027V060	40	27	60	So Joseph took the body, and wrapped it in a clean linen cloth, and laid it in his own new tomb, which he had cut in the rock; and after rolling a great stone against the opening of the tomb, he went away.
B040C027V061	40	27	61	And Mary Magdalene was there, and the other Mary, sitting opposite the tomb.
B040C027V062	40	27	62	The day after - that is, the day following the Preparation - the chief priests and Pharisees went in a body to Pilate and said.
B040C027V063	40	27	63	"We recollect, Sir, that when he was living this imposter said, I will rise again after three days.
B040C027V064	40	27	64	Now therefore give order to have the sepulcher securely guarded until the third day, for fear his disciples may come and steal him away, and then tell the people, He is risen from the dead;and so the last error will be worse than the first."
B040C027V065	40	27	65	"You can have a guard," said Pilate. "Go your way, make it as secure as you can."
B040C027V066	40	27	66	So they went and made the sepulcher secure, by sealing the stone in the presence of the guard.
B040C028V001	40	28	1	At the end of the Sabbath, as it began to dawn toward the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary came down to see the sepulcher, when lo!
B040C028V002	40	28	2	There had been a great earthquake; for an angel of the Lord had come down from heaven, and gone and rolled away the stone, and was sitting upon it.
B040C028V003	40	28	3	His appearance was like lightning, and his raiment white as snow.
B040C028V004	40	28	4	The guards trembled for fear of him, and became like dead men.
B040C028V005	40	28	5	But to the women the angel said. "You need have no fear, for I know that you are seeking Jesus, the Crucified One.
B040C028V006	40	28	6	He is not here; for he is risen, even as he said. Come, see the place where the Master was lying!
B040C028V007	40	28	7	And go quickly and tell his disciples. He is risen from the dead;  he goes before you into Galilee; you will see him there. Remember, I have told you."
B040C028V008	40	28	8	On this they ran quickly from the sepulcher, in fear and great joy,  to tell the news to his disciples.
B040C028V009	40	28	9	And behold! Jesus himself met them, saying, "All hail!" And they went up to him and clasped his feet and worshiped him.
B040C028V010	40	28	10	Then Jesus said to them. "Fear not! Go tell my brothers to depart into Galilee, and they will see men there."
B040C028V011	40	28	11	Now while they were on their way, some of the guard went into the city and told the high priest all that had happened.
B040C028V012	40	28	12	And when they had met with the elders and conferred together, they heavily bribed the soldiers and told them to say,
B040C028V013	40	28	13	"His disciples came by night and stole him away, while we were asleep."
B040C028V014	40	28	14	"If this should reach the Governors ears," they said, "we will satisfy him and screen you from punishment."
B040C028V015	40	28	15	So the soldiers took the money, and did as they were told; and this story has been noised abroad among the Jews, and continues to this day.
B040C028V016	40	28	16	But the eleven disciples went away to Galilee, to the mountain where Jesus had appointed them.
B040C028V017	40	28	17	And when they saw him they worshiped him; but some doubted.
B040C028V018	40	28	18	And Jesus came forward to them and spoke to them, saying. "All authority has been given to me in heaven and on earth.
B040C028V019	40	28	19	Go, therefore, and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them into the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit;
B040C028V020	40	28	20	teaching them to observe every command which I have given you. and lo! I am with you alway, even unto the end of the world."
B041C001V001	41	1	1	Beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;
B041C001V002	41	1	2	even as it is written in the prophet Isaiah, Behold, I am sending my messenger before your face to prepare your way.
B041C001V003	41	1	3	The voice of one crying aloud. In the desert make ready a road for the Lord. Make his paths straight.
B041C001V004	41	1	4	In the desert came Johnwho baptized, and preached a baptism of repentance for the remission of sins;
B041C001V005	41	1	5	and all the land of Judea, and all the people of Jerusalem, kept going out to him, and were baptized by him in the Jordan river,  confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	And Johnwas clothed with camels hair, and he had a leather girdle round his loins, and he ate locusts, and "honey of the wood."
B041C001V007	41	1	7	He made proclamation. "There is One mightier than I coming after me,  and I am not worthy to stoop down and unfasten his sandal strap;
B041C001V008	41	1	8	I have baptized you in water, but he shall baptize you in the Holy Spirit."
B041C001V009	41	1	9	It was at that time that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized by Johnin the Jordan;
B041C001V010	41	1	10	and as soon as he rose from the water he saw the sky cleft asunder,  and the Spirit like a dove descending upon him,
B041C001V011	41	1	11	and a voice from the sky. "Thou art my Son, my beloved; in thee is my delight."
B041C001V012	41	1	12	Then the Spirit drove him at once into the desert,
B041C001V013	41	1	13	and he remained in the desert for forty days, tempted by Satan; and he was among the wild beasts, but the angels were ministering to him.
B041C001V014	41	1	14	After Johnhad been thrown into prison Jesus came into Galilee preaching the gospel of God.
B041C001V015	41	1	15	"The time is now come," he said, "and the kingdom of God is near!  Repent and believe the gospel."
B041C001V016	41	1	16	And as he was passing along by the sea of Galilee he saw Simon and Andrew, Simons brother, casting their net into the sea, for they were fishermen;
B041C001V017	41	1	17	so Jesus said to them, "Come after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men."
B041C001V018	41	1	18	At once they left their nets and followed him.
B041C001V019	41	1	19	As he went a little farther on he saw James, the son of Zebedee, and Johnhis brother, who also were in their boat mending the nets.
B041C001V020	41	1	20	Straightway he called them, and they left their father Zebedee in the ship with the hired servants and went after him.
B041C001V021	41	1	21	So they came to Capernaum, and as soon as the Sabbath Day came he went into the synagogue and began to teach.
B041C001V022	41	1	22	They were astonished at his teaching, for he was teaching them with authority, not like the Scribes.
B041C001V023	41	1	23	And at that very moment, there in their synagogue, a man in the grip of an unclean spirit shrieked out.
B041C001V024	41	1	24	"What business have you with us, you Jesus of Nazareth? Are you come to destroy us? I know you who you are, the Holy One of God."
B041C001V025	41	1	25	But Jesus rebuked him, saying. "Be quit! Come out of him."
B041C001V026	41	1	26	So the unclean spirit, after tearing him, came out of him with a loud cry;
B041C001V027	41	1	27	and every one was amazed so that they began questioning among themselves. "What does this mean? A new teaching with authority? He lays commands even upon unclean spirits and they obey him."
B041C001V028	41	1	28	And at once his fame spread everywhere through that part of Galilee.
B041C001V029	41	1	29	On leaving the synagogue they went at once with Jamesand Johnto the house of Simon and Andrew.
B041C001V030	41	1	30	Now Simons mother-in-law lay sick of fever, and without delay they told him about her.
B041C001V031	41	1	31	So he came and took her hand and raised her up. The fever left her at once, and she began to wait upon them.
B041C001V032	41	1	32	At evening when the sun had set, people came and brought to him all the sick and demon-possessed,
B041C001V033	41	1	33	and the whole town was gathered at the door.
B041C001V034	41	1	34	He cured many who were ill with various diseases, and drove out many demons. But he did not allow the demons to speak, because they knew who he was.
B041C001V035	41	1	35	In the morning he rose a great while before day and went out to a desert place, and there prayed.
B041C001V036	41	1	36	And Simon and his companions hunted him up,
B041C001V037	41	1	37	and told him, "Every one is looking for you."
B041C001V038	41	1	38	"Let us go away," he answered, "to the neighboring country towns,  that I may preach there, too; because for that purpose I came forth."
B041C001V039	41	1	39	So he went throughout Galilee, preaching in the synagogues and driving out demons.
B041C001V040	41	1	40	One day a leper cane to him and besought him as he knelt down to him, saying, "If you choose, you are able to cleanse me."
B041C001V041	41	1	41	Jesus, moved with compassion, put out his hand and touched him,  saying, "I do choose, be clean!"
B041C001V042	41	1	42	The leprosy at once left him, and he was made clean.
B041C001V043	41	1	43	Jesus immediately sent him away, charging him sternly and saying.
B041C001V044	41	1	44	"See you say nothing to any one; but go your way, show yourself to the priest, and offer for your purification what Moses commanded for a testimony to them."
B041C001V045	41	1	45	But he went out and began to tell every one and to publish it broadcast, so that Jesus could no longer enter any town openly; but he had to remain outside in lonely places, and people kept coming to him from every quarter.
B041C002V001	41	2	1	Some days later when Jesus entered Capernaum again the news spread,  "He is in the house";
B041C002V002	41	2	2	and at once such a crowd gathered that there was no longer room for them, even around the door.
B041C002V003	41	2	3	While he was speaking his message, they came bringing to him a paralytic, carried by four men.
B041C002V004	41	2	4	When they could not get him near to Jesus because of the crowd, they removed the roof under which he stood, and after making an opening,  they let down the cot on which the paralytic was lying.
B041C002V005	41	2	5	Then Jesus, when he perceived their faith, said to the paralytic,  "Son your sins are forgiven."
B041C002V006	41	2	6	But there were some Scribes sitting there who reasoned in their hearts.
B041C002V007	41	2	7	"Why does this man speak like this? He blasphemes. Who is able to forgive sins but One, God himself?"
B041C002V008	41	2	8	Jesus clearly perceived at once be the Spirit that they were thus reasoning in their hearts and said to them.
B041C002V009	41	2	9	"Why do you reason thus in your hearts? Which is easier, to say to the paralytic, Your sins are forgiven, or to say, Rise, take up your cot and walk?
B041C002V010	41	2	10	But to let you see that the Son of man has authority on earth to forgive sins" -he said to the paralytic-
B041C002V011	41	2	11	"I bid you rise, take up your cot, and go home."
B041C002V012	41	2	12	The man rose, at once took up his cot, and went out before them all;  at which they were all astounded, and gave God glory, saying, "We never saw anything like this."
B041C002V013	41	2	13	Then Jesus went again to the seaside, and the whole crowd kept coming to him, and he taught them.
B041C002V014	41	2	14	As he was passing by he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus, sitting in the tax-office; and he said to him, "Follow me." So he rose and followed him.
B041C002V015	41	2	15	Later on Levi was sitting at table in his house, and together with Jesus and his disciples a number of tax-gatherers and sinners were guests, for there were many of them who used to follow him.
B041C002V016	41	2	16	But when some scribes of the Pharisees saw him eating with the sinners and tax-gatherers, they said to his disciples, "Is he eating and drinking with tax-gatherers and sinners?"
