B041C008V001	41	8	1	In those days when a large crowd had again assembled and had nothing to eat, Jesus called together his disciples and said to them.
B041C008V002	41	8	2	"My heart aches for the crowd, because they have remained with me three days now, and they have nothing to eat;
B041C008V003	41	8	3	and if I send them away fasting to their homes, they will faint on the way. Moreover, some of them are from a distance."
B041C008V004	41	8	4	"Where will it be possible," answered his disciples, "for one to fill these men with bread in a lonely place like this?"
B041C008V005	41	8	5	He asked them, "How many loaves have you?" "Seven," they said.
