B041C015V031	41	15	31	In the same way the high priests also, as well as the Scribes, kept on mocking him to themselves. "He saved others," they said, "but himself he cannot save.
B041C015V032	41	15	32	The Christ! The King of Israel! Let him now come down from the cross, that we may see and believe." They also who had been crucified with Jesus kept reviling him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	At noon a darkness came over the whole country, lasting until three in the afternoon.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	At three oclock Jesus cried in a loud voice, "Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani?" which means, "My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?"
B041C015V035	41	15	35	When they heard this, some of the bystanders said, "Listen, he is calling for Elijah."
B041C015V036	41	15	36	Then a man ran and filled a sponge full of sour wine, and put it on a stick, and offered it to him to drink, saying, "Wait, let us see whether Elijah will come to take him down!"
B041C015V037	41	15	37	But Jesus uttered a loud cry and expired.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	And the curtain of the Sanctuary was torn in two from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	Then the army captain, who was standing facing Jesus when he thus died, said, "in truth this man was a Son of God."
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were some women also watching from a distance. Among them were both Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of Jamesthe younger and of Joses, and Salome,
B041C015V041	41	15	41	women who used to follow him when he was in Galilee, and minister to him; and many other women who had come up to Jerusalem with him.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	Toward sunset, as it was the preparation (that is the day preceding the Sabbath),
B041C015V043	41	15	43	there came Joseph of Arimathea, a Councilor, honorable in rank, who was himself also looking for the kingdom of God. He boldly went in to Pilate to ask for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	But Pilate wondered whether he were already dead. So he summoned the army captain, and inquired if he had been any time dead;
B041C015V045	41	15	45	and when he learned the fact from the army captain he gave the body to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	So Joseph bought him a sheet, and took Jesus down, wound him in the sheet, and laid him in a tomb which had been hewn out of a rock, and then rolled a stone against the opening of the tomb;
B041C015V047	41	15	47	and Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses were watching to see where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	When the Sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of James, and Salome brought spices in order to go and anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And very early in the morning, on the first day of the week, they came to the tomb as the sun was rising;
B041C016V003	41	16	3	and they kept saying to one another, "Who will roll away the stone for us from the door of the tomb?"
B041C016V004	41	16	4	But then as they looked up they saw that the stone, which was a very large one, was already rolled away;
B041C016V005	41	16	5	and upon entering the tomb they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a white robe.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	They were terrified, but he said to them. "Do not be terrified! You are seeking Jesus the Nazarene, who was crucified? He is risen; he is not here. See, the place where they laid him!
