B042C001V001	42	1	1	Seeing that many have taken it in hand to draw up an account of those matters which have been fully established among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as they reported them to us, who were from beginning eye-  witnesses and ministers of the word,
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it seemed good to me also accurately, from the very beginning, to write them to you in order, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	so that you may know the certainty of the story which you have been taught by the word of mouth.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	In the reign of Herod, King of Judea, there was a certain priest,  named Zachariah, belonging to the class of Abijah. He had a wife named Elizabeth,
B042C001V006	42	1	6	who was a descendant of Aaron. They were both righteous in the sight of the Lord, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the law, blameless.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	Now they had no child, for Elizabeth was barren, and both were far advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	Now while Zachariah was acting as priest before God in the due course of his class, it fell to his lot, according to the custom of priesthood,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	to enter into the sanctuary of the Lord and to burn incense.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And the whole multitude of the people were without, praying at the hour of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	Then there appeared to him an angel of the Lord, standing on the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And as he saw him Zachariah was troubled, and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the Angel said to him. "Do not be afraid, Zachariah, because your petition has been heard, and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and you are to call him John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	"And he shall be to you a joy and an exultation, and many shall rejoice over his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	"For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, "He shall drink neither wine nor strong drink, "He shall be filled with the Holy Spirit from the hour of his birth,
B042C001V016	42	1	16	"And shall win many of the sons of Israel to the Lord, their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	"He shall go before Him in the wisdom and power of Elijah to turn the hearts of the fathers to their children and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, and so to make ready for the Lord a people prepared for him."
B042C001V018	42	1	18	"How shall I be sure of this?" said Zachariah to the Angel. "For I am an old man and my wife is advanced in years."
B042C001V019	42	1	19	"I am Gabriel," answered the angel, "who stand in the presence of God; and I have been sent to speak to you and to bring and to bring you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	"And now you shall be silent and unable to speak until the day the day when this has taken place; because you did not believe my words -  Words which will be fulfilled at their appointed time."
B042C001V021	42	1	21	Meanwhile the people were waiting for Zachariah and wondering why he stayed so long in the sanctuary.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	And when he came out he could not speak to them, and then they knew that he had seen a vision in the sanctuary. He kept making signs to them and remained dumb.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	As soon as his term of priestly service was ended he went home;
B042C001V024	42	1	24	and after those days Elizabeth, his wife, Conceived, and she hid herself five months, saying.
B042C001V025	42	1	25	"This has the Lord done for me. He has now deigned to take the away my reproach among men."
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Six months later the angel Gabriel was sent by God to a town in Galilee, called Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a maiden betrothed to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David.  Her name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	The angel went in and said to her. "Joy to you, highly favored one!  "The Lord is with you."
B042C001V029	42	1	29	Mary was greatly agitated at his word, and was revolving in her mind what this salutation could mean.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	when the angel said to her. "Fear not Mary, for you have found grace with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	"And behold, you shall conceive in your womb and bear a son; and you shall call his name Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	"He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Most High.  "And the Lord God will give him the throne of his forefather David,
B042C001V033	42	1	33	"and he shall reign over the House of Jacob forever; and of his kingdom there shall be no end."
B042C001V034	42	1	34	And Mary said to the angel. "How can this be? For I have no husband?"
B042C001V035	42	1	35	"The Holy Spirit shall come upon you," said the angel, "and the power of the most High shall overshadow you, and therefore the holy offspring which is born, shall be called the son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	"And behold your kinswoman, Elizabeth, she also has conceived a son in her old age, and this was the sixth month with her that was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	"For no word of God shall be void of power."
B042C001V038	42	1	38	Then Mary said. "Behold I am Lords slave. Let it be to me as you have said." Then the angel departed from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	Soon after this Mary set out and hastened unto the hill-country to a town in Judah;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and there she came into the house of Zachariah, and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And when Elizabeth heard her salutation, the babe leaped in her womb, and Elizabeth herself was filled with the Holy Spirit,
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and called out with a loud cry. "Blessed are you among women, and blessed is your unborn child!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	"But why is this honor done me, that the mother of my Lord should come me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	"For behold when the sound of your salutation reached my ears, the babe leaped with joy within my womb.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	"And blessed is she who believed that the Lords words spoken to her would be fulfilled."
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said. "My soul doth magnify the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	"My spirit exults in the God, who is my Saviour,
B042C001V048	42	1	48	"For he has regarded the humiliation of his slave, And from this hour all ages will count me blessed.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	"For he who is mighty has done great things for me; And holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	"His mercy is unto generations and generations on those who reverence him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	"He has showed strength with his arm. "He has scattered proud in the imagination of their hearts;
B042C001V052	42	1	52	"he has put down princes from their thrones, and has exalted those of low degree.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	"The hungry he has filled with good things, But the rich he has sent empty away.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	"He has helped Israel, his servant, that he might remember mercy,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	"As he spoke to our forefathers, to Abraham and his offspring forever."
B042C001V056	42	1	56	So Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months and returned home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now when the time of Elizabeths delivery was come, she gave birth to a son;
B042C001V058	42	1	58	and her neighbors and kinsfolk heard that the Lord had magnified his mercy toward her; and they rejoiced with her,
B042C001V059	42	1	59	and came on the eighth day to circumcise the child. They were about to call him "Zachariah," after his father,
B042C001V060	42	1	60	when his mother said, "No, he is to be called John."
B042C001V061	42	1	61	Said they, "You have no relatives of that name!"
B042C001V062	42	1	62	Then they asked his father by signs what he wished to call the child.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	So he asked for a writing tablet and wrote down, "His name is John."
B042C001V064	42	1	64	Every one was surprised, and at once his mouth was opened and his tongue loosed, and he spoke, blessing God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And there came a great fear upon all in the neighborhood; and throughout the hill country of Judea all these sayings were much talked about.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	All the story laid it up in their hearts, saying "What, then, will this child be?" For the Lords hands was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And his father, Zachariah, was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied, saying.
B042C001V068	42	1	68	"Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, For he has visited and redeemed his people,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	"And has raised up a mighty Deliverer for us In the house of his servant David,
B042C001V070	42	1	70	"As he spake by the mouth of his holy Prophets Which have been since the world began
B042C001V071	42	1	71	To deliver us from our enemies, and from the power Of all who hate us.
B042C001V072	42	1	72	"He showed mercy to our forefathers, He remembered his holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	"The oath which he swore to Abraham, our forefather,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	"That he we should be delivered out of the Hand of our enemies, And should serve him without fear,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	"In holiness and righteousness before him All our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	"And thou, child, shalt be called the Prophet of the Most High, For thou shalt go before the Lord to prepare the way
B042C001V077	42	1	77	"To give to his people a knowledge of salvation Through the remission of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	"Through the heart of mercy of our God, Whereby the Dayspring from on high shall visit us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	"To give light to those who sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, And to guide our feet into the paths of peace."
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child grew, and became strong in the Spirit, and remained in the desert till the day of his showing to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	In those days Augustus Caesar issued an edict for a census of the whole inhabited world.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	This was the first census, When Quirinius was governor of Syria.
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And every one went to be registered, each to the town to which he belonged.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city if Nazareth,  into Judea, to Davids town of Bethlehem, because he was of the house and family of David.
B042C002V005	42	2	5	He went to be registered along with Mary, who was espoused to him,  and was pregnant.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	But while they were there the days were fulfilled for her delivery.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she gave birth to her firstborn son; and she wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger because there was no room for them in the inn.
