B042C004V001	42	4	1	Then Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, came back from the Jordan, and was led by the Spirit into the desert for forty days, all the time tempted by the devil.
B042C004V002	42	4	2	He ate nothing during these days, and at the close of them he was hungry.
B042C004V003	42	4	3	The devil said to him, "If you are the Son of God tell this stone to become bread."
B042C004V004	42	4	4	And Jesus answered him, saying, "It is written that not by bread alone shall man live."
B042C004V005	42	4	5	And the devil led him up and showed him all the kingdoms of the inhabited earth in an instant of time, and the devil said to him.
B042C004V006	42	4	6	"To you will I give all this authority and this glory; for it has been handed over to me, and I give it to whomever I wish.
B042C004V007	42	4	7	"If then you will worship me, it shall all be yours."
B042C004V008	42	4	8	"It is written," answered Jesus, "Thou shalt worship the Lord, thy God, and him only shalt thou serve."
B042C004V009	42	4	9	Then he brought him to Jerusalem, and caused him to stand upon the Temple roof, and said to him. "If you really are the Son of God throw yourself down here;
B042C004V010	42	4	10	for it is written, "He shall give his angels charge of thee, to guard thee safely;
B042C004V011	42	4	11	"They will bear thee up in their hands, Lest thou dash thy food against a stone."
B042C004V012	42	4	12	"It has been said," replied Jesus, "Thou shalt not tempt the Lord,  thy God."
B042C004V013	42	4	13	So, after exhausting on him every kind of temptation, the devil left him for a time.
B042C004V014	42	4	14	Then Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit to Galilee, and his fame spread throughout all the surrounding country,
B042C004V015	42	4	15	and he began to teach in their synagogues, and was glorified by all.
B042C004V016	42	4	16	Then he came to Nazareth where he had been brought up. and, as was his custom, he entered into the synagogue on the Sabbath Day, and stood up to read.
B042C004V017	42	4	17	And there was handed him the roll of the prophet Isaiah; and unrolling it he found the place where it was written,
B042C004V018	42	4	18	The Spirit of the Lord is upon me Because He has anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor, He has sent me to proclaim release to the prisoners, And recovery of sight to the blind; To set at liberty those that are bruised,
B042C004V019	42	4	19	To proclaim the acceptable year of the Lord.
B042C004V020	42	4	20	Then rolling up the papyrus, he gave it back to the attendant and sat down.
B042C004V021	42	4	21	The eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on him, and he began to say to them, "Today is this scripture fulfilled in your hearing."
B042C004V022	42	4	22	And they all spoke well of him, and marveled at the words of charm that fell from his lips. "Is not this the son of Joseph?" they asked.
B042C004V023	42	4	23	Jesus answered. "Doubtless you will quote the proverb to me,  "Physician, heal thyself! Do also here in your own country all that we hear that you have done in Capernaum."
B042C004V024	42	4	24	"I tell you in solemn truth," he added, "that no prophet is acceptable in his own country.
B042C004V025	42	4	25	In very truth I tell you there were many widows in Israel in the days of Elijah, when the heavens were closed for three years and six months, when a great famine came over all the land;
B042C004V026	42	4	26	"yet Elijah was not sent to any one of them, but only to a widow in Zarephath in Sidon.
B042C004V027	42	4	27	"And there were many lepers in Israel in the days of the prophet Elisha, yet none of them was cleansed but only Naaman the Syrian."
B042C004V028	42	4	28	When they had heard these words, those in the synagogue were filled with fury;
B042C004V029	42	4	29	they rose, hurried him outside the town, and brought him to the brow of the hill on which their city was built, intending to cast him down headlong.
B042C004V030	42	4	30	But he, passing through the midst of them, took his departure.
B042C004V031	42	4	31	Then he went down to Capernaum, a city of Galilee, and continued to teach the people on the Sabbath Days.
B042C004V032	42	4	32	They were deeply impressed by his teaching because his speech was with authority.
B042C004V033	42	4	33	And there was in the synagogue a man possessed by the spirit of a foul demon. He cried out, in a loud voice, saying.
B042C004V034	42	4	34	"Ha! Jesus of Nazareth, what business have you with us? Are you come to destroy us? I know you who you are, you holy one of God!"
B042C004V035	42	4	35	And Jesus rebuked him, saying. "Be quiet! Come out of him." And when the demon had thrown the man down before them, he came out of him without doing him any harm.
B042C004V036	42	4	36	All were amazed, and began to ask one another, saying. "What is this word? For with authority and power he commands the unclean spirits and they come out."
B042C004V037	42	4	37	And the talk about him spread into every locality in the surrounding country.
B042C004V038	42	4	38	Now when he rose and left the synagogue, he entered into the house of Simon, where Simons mother-in-law lay sick of a great fever. And they kept entreating him for her.
B042C004V039	42	4	39	And he stood over her and rebuked the fever, and it left her; and at once she arose and ministered unto them.
B042C004V040	42	4	40	At sunset all they who had any sick with any sort of disease brought them to him; and he laid his hands on every one of them and healed them.
B042C004V041	42	4	41	Demons also came out of many, screaming and saying, "You are the Son of God." But he rebuked them, and did not permit them to speak,  because they knew that he was the Christ.
B042C004V042	42	4	42	And when it was daybreak he left the town, and went away to a solitary place; and the crowd kept seeking him. Coming at length upon him, they attempted to detain him so that he should not leave them.
B042C004V043	42	4	43	But he said to them. "I must preach the gospel of the kingdom of God to the other towns also; for that is what I was sent to do."
B042C004V044	42	4	44	So he continued to preach in the synagogues of Galilee.
B042C005V001	42	5	1	On one occasion when he was standing by the lake of Gennesaret, the crowd pressed upon him to listen to the word of God.
B042C005V002	42	5	2	But he saw two fishing-boats on the shore of the lake; the fishermen had disembarked and were washing their nets.
B042C005V003	42	5	3	He went on board one of the boats which belonged to Simon, and asked him to push out a little way from land. Then he sat down and continued to teach the crowd from the boat.
B042C005V004	42	5	4	When he had finished speaking, he said to Simon, "Push out into deep water, and let down your nets for a haul."
B042C005V005	42	5	5	"Master," answered Simon, "although we toiled all night, we took nothing; but at your bidding I will let down the nets."
B042C005V006	42	5	6	And when they had done this they enclosed a great multitude of fish;  and their nets began to break.
B042C005V007	42	5	7	So they motioned to their partners in the other boat to come and help them. They came and filled both boats, so that they began to sink.
