B042C006V021	42	6	21	"Blessed are you who are hungry now, For you shall be filled.  "Blessed are you who are wailing now, For you shall laugh.
B042C006V022	42	6	22	"Blessed are you when men shall hate you, And excommunicate you and reproach you, and cast out your name as evil because of the Son of man.
B042C006V023	42	6	23	"Rejoice in that day and exult, For your reward is great in heaven;  For even so did their fathers to the prophets.
B042C006V024	42	6	24	"But woe to you rich! For you already have received your consolation.
B042C006V025	42	6	25	"Woe unto you who are full now! For you shall suffer hunger. "Woe to you who are laughing now! For you shall wail and weep.
B042C006V026	42	6	26	"Woe to you when all men shall speak well of you! For even so did their fathers to the false prophets.
B042C006V027	42	6	27	"But to you who are listening to me I say, Love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,
B042C006V028	42	6	28	Bless those who curse you, pray for those who calumniate you.
B042C006V029	42	6	29	To him who gives you a blow on the jaw Turn the other jaw also; And from him who is robbing you of your cloak Withhold not your coat also.
B042C006V030	42	6	30	Give to every one who asks you; And do not demand your goods back from him who is taking them away.
B042C006V031	42	6	31	And as you would like men to do to you, So do you also to them.
B042C006V032	42	6	32	"If you love those who love you what credit is it to you? Why even sinners love those who love them.
B042C006V033	42	6	33	"And if you are kind to those who are kind to you, what credit is it to you? Even sinners do the same.
B042C006V034	42	6	34	"And if you lend to those from whom you are hoping to receive, what credit is that to you? Even sinners lend to sinners, so as to get as much back.
B042C006V035	42	6	35	"But you must love even your enemies and be kind to them, And lend,  despairing of no man. Then your reward will be great, And you will be the sons of the Most High; For he is kind even to the ungrateful and to the evil.
B042C006V036	42	6	36	"Do you therefore be merciful, As your Father is merciful.
B042C006V037	42	6	37	"Do not judge, and you shall not be judged; Do not condemn, and you shall not be condemned;
B042C006V038	42	6	38	"Pardon, and you shall be pardoned; Give, and gifts shall be given to you; Full measure, pressed down, shaken together, running over,  they shall pour into your bosom. For with what measure you measure,  they will measure back to you."
B042C006V039	42	6	39	He also told them a parable. "Can a blind man lead a blind man? Will they not both fall into a pit?
B042C006V040	42	6	40	"There is no disciple who is above his master; But every one when he is completely trained will be like his master.
B042C006V041	42	6	41	"And why do you look at the splinter that is in your brothers eye,  but never consider the beam that is in your own eye?
B042C006V042	42	6	42	"Or how can you say to your brother. "Brother, allow me to pull that splinter out of your eye," when you do not see the beam in your own eye? Hypocrite! Take out first the beam from your own eye, and then you will see clearly to take out the splinter from your brothers eye.
B042C006V043	42	6	43	"For there is not good tree which bears worthless fruit, nor again any worthless tree which bears good fruit; for each tree is known by its own fruit.
B042C006V044	42	6	44	"You do not gather figs from thorns, and grapes are not plucked from a bramble-bush.
B042C006V045	42	6	45	"The good man out of the good treasure-house of his heart brings forth good; and the evil man out of the evil treasure-house of his heart brings forth evil; for the mouth speaks out of the abundance of the heart.
B042C006V046	42	6	46	"And why are you calling me Lord, Lord, and not doing what I tell you?
B042C006V047	42	6	47	"I will show whom the man that comes to me, and listens to my works,  and does them, is like.
B042C006V048	42	6	48	"He is like a man who is building a house who digged and went deep and laid a foundation upon rock. And, when a flood came, the torrent dashed against that house, but could not move, because it had been founded upon rock.
B042C006V049	42	6	49	"But he who listens but does not do, is like a man who built a house upon the soil, without foundations, against which the torrent burst,  and at once it fell in, and the ruin of that house was great."
