B042C016V001	42	16	1	To his disciples he said. "There was a certain rich man who had a steward, and this steward was accused to him of wasting his property.
B042C016V002	42	16	2	"He called to him to him and said. "What is this that I hear about you? Render an account of your stewardship; for you can no longer be steward.
B042C016V003	42	16	3	"Now the steward said to himself. What shall I do, now that my master is taking away my stewardship? I am not strong enough to dig,  to beg I am ashamed.
B042C016V004	42	16	4	"I know what I will do, so that when I am put out of my stewardship, they may receive me into their houses.
B042C016V005	42	16	5	"So he called to him each of his masters debtors and said to the first, How much money do you owe my master?
B042C016V006	42	16	6	"A hundred measures of oil, he answered. "He said to him, Take your bill and sit down quickly and write fifty."
B042C016V007	42	16	7	"To a second he said, How much do you owe? "The man answered, A hundred measures of wheat. "Here is you bill, he said, change it to eighty measures.
B042C016V008	42	16	8	"And the master praised the unjust steward because he had acted shrewdly; for the sons of this world are in relation to their own generation wiser than the sons of the light.
B042C016V009	42	16	9	"And to you I say, Use mammon, dishonest as it is, to make yourselves friends, so that when it shall fail they will welcome you to the eternal tabernacles.
B042C016V010	42	16	10	"The man who is faithful in a very little is faithful also in much,  and he who is unjust in a very little, is unjust also as much.
B042C016V011	42	16	11	"If therefore you have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon,  who will trust to you the true riches?
B042C016V012	42	16	12	"And if you are not faithful with what belongs to another, who will give you what is your own?
B042C016V013	42	16	13	"No one can be a household servants to two masters; for either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will cling to the one and despise the other. You cannot be the slave of God and of Mammon."
B042C016V014	42	16	14	Now the Pharisees who loved money listened to all this and they jeered at him.
B042C016V015	42	16	15	He said to them. "You are those that justify themselves in the eyes of men; but God knows you hearts; for that which is lofty in the eyes of men is abomination in the eyes of God.
B042C016V016	42	16	16	"The Law and the Prophet lasted until John; since then the gospel of the kingdom of God is preached, and any one presses in.
B042C016V017	42	16	17	"Yet it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away then for one title of the law to fail.
