B042C016V019	42	16	19	"Now there was a certain rich man who was clothed in purple and fine linen, and made merry every day in splendor.
B042C016V020	42	16	20	"And a certain beggar named Lazarus was thrown at his door.
B042C016V021	42	16	21	"He was full of sores, and longingly desired to be fed with the crumbs that fell from the rich mans table. Yes! even the dogs came and licked his sores.
