B042C018V001	42	18	1	He also taught them by a parable how they ought always to pray and never to lose heart.
B042C018V002	42	18	2	"There was a certain town," he said, "a judge who had neither reverence for God, nor respect for man.
B042C018V003	42	18	3	"In that same town there was a widow who came again and again before him, saying, "Do for me the justice of my adversary.
