B042C024V001	42	24	1	On the Sabbath Day they rested in obedience to the commandment, but in the deep dawn of the first day of the week they took the spices which they had prepared, and came to the tomb.
B042C024V002	42	24	2	And they found the stone rolled away from the tomb,
B042C024V003	42	24	3	and on entering they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	While they were still perplexed over this, it happened that the two men stood near them in dazzling raiment.
B042C024V005	42	24	5	They were terrified, and bowed down their faces to the ground, but the men said to them. "Why are you seeking him who lives among the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	"He is not here; he is risen. Do you remember how he told you when he was still in Galilee
B042C024V007	42	24	7	that the Son of man had to be betrayed into the hands of sinful men,  and to be crucified, and to rise on the third day?"
B042C024V008	42	24	8	Then they recollected his words,
B042C024V009	42	24	9	and turning away from the tomb they told all this to the eleven, and to all the rest.
B042C024V010	42	24	10	It was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, and Mary, the mother of James, and the rest of the women who were telling all this to the apostles.
B042C024V011	42	24	11	But the whole story seemed to them but an idle tale; and they disbelieved the women.
B042C024V012	42	24	12	Peter, however, got up and ran to the tomb, but when he stooped and looked in he saw the linen wrappings by themselves, and he departed to his home, wondering at that which was come to pass.
B042C024V013	42	24	13	On that same day two of his disciples were walking to Emmaus, a village about seven miles from Jerusalem.
B042C024V014	42	24	14	They were talking together about all these events,
B042C024V015	42	24	15	and as they talked and discussed matter, Jesus himself drew near and began walking beside them.
B042C024V016	42	24	16	But their eyes continued to be held that they should not recognize him even for an instant,
B042C024V017	42	24	17	And he said to them, "What words are these that you are exchanging one with another, as you walk along?"
B042C024V018	42	24	18	They stood still, looking sad. And one of them named Cleopas,  answered him, "Do you sojourn alone in Jerusalem, that you do not know what things have been happening there these days?"
B042C024V019	42	24	19	"What kind of things?" he answered. And they said. "The things concerning Jesus of Nazareth, who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people;
B042C024V020	42	24	20	"and how our high priest and ruler delivered him to be condemned to death and crucified him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	"But we were hoping that it was he who should redeem Israel. Yes,  and besides all this is the third day since these things happened.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	"Moreover, some women of our company amazed us. They went to his tomb at daybreak,
B042C024V023	42	24	23	"and found that his body was not there; then they came and told us that besides they had seen a vision of angels, who said that he was alive.
B042C024V024	42	24	24	"Thereupon some of our own party to the tomb, and found it even so as the women had said, but him they did not see."
B042C024V025	42	24	25	"O foolish men," said Jesus, "slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken!
B042C024V026	42	24	26	"Behooved it not the Christ to suffer thus, and then to enter into his glory?"
B042C024V027	42	24	27	And beginning with Moses and the Prophets, he interpreted all the passages concerning himself.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	When they drew near to the village to which they are were going, he appeared to be going farther.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	But they urged him to stay with them, saying, "Abide with us, for it is toward evening, and the day is now far spent."
B042C024V030	42	24	30	So he went in to stay with them. But as he sat down with them, and took bread, and had blessed and broken it, and was handing it to them,
B042C024V031	42	24	31	their eyes were opened, and they recognized him, and he vanished out of their sight.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	"Were not our hearts burning within us," they said to each other,  "while we were talking with him on the way, and he was opening to us the scriptures?"
B042C024V033	42	24	33	So they rose and returned to Jerusalem that very hour, and found the Eleven and the others all met together,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	saying, "The Lord is really risen, and has appeared to Simon!"
B042C024V035	42	24	35	Then they began to tell what happened on the road, and he was known to them when he broke the bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	While they were yet speaking he stood among them and said, "Peace be to you!"
B042C024V037	42	24	37	They were startled and terrified and thought that they were seeing a ghost.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	And he said to them. "Why are you disturbed? And why do questions rise in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	"Look at my hands and my feet. It is I! Feel me and see; for a ghost has not flesh and blood as I have."
B042C024V040	42	24	40	Then he showed them his hands and feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	But while they still did not believe it for joy, and were filled with wonder, he asked them, "Have you anything here to eat?"
B042C024V042	42	24	42	So they gave him a piece of broiled fish,
B042C024V043	42	24	43	and he took it and ate it in their presence.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	Then he said to them, "These are my words which I spoke to you while I was still with you, how all things must be fulfilled which are written in the Law of Moses, and the prophets, and the Psalms concerning me."
B042C024V045	42	24	45	Then he opened their minds to understand the Scriptures,
B042C024V046	42	24	46	and he said. "Thus it is written that the Christ should suffer and rise again from the dead, the third day;
B042C024V047	42	24	47	"and that repentance unto remission of sins should be preached in his name unto all the nations, beginning from Jerusalem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	"You must bear testimony to this.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	"And I will send forth the promise of my Father upon you. But tarry in Jerusalem until you are clothed with power from on high."
B042C024V050	42	24	50	And he led them out until they were over against Bethany; and he lifted up his hands and blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	And it happened that while he was blessing them, that he parted from them and was carried into heaven.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	And they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy,
B042C024V053	42	24	53	and were continually in the temple, blessing God.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was face to face with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	He was face to face with God in the Beginning.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things came into being through him, and apart from him nothing that exists came into being.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and the life was the light of men.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light is shining in the darkness, and the darkness has not overwhelmed it
B043C001V006	43	1	6	A man came into being, sent from God, whose name was John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	He came as a witness, that he might bear testimony concerning the Light - so that all men might believe through him.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the Light; it was to bear testimony concerning the Light that he came into being.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	The true Light, which enlightens every man, was then coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and through him the world came into being, yet the world knew him not.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own creation, and his own folk welcomed him not.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But to all who receive him, to them he has given the right to become children of God, even to those who trust in his name;
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word became flesh and tented with us. And we gazed on his glory - glory as of the Fathers only Son - full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John bore witness concerning him, and cried aloud, saying, "This is he of whom I said, He who is coming after me has been put before me,  for he was before me."
B043C001V016	43	1	16	For out of his fulness we have all received, yes, grace upon grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the Law was given by Moses, but grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No man has ever seen God; God, only begotten, who is in the bosom of the Father - he has interpreted him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	Now this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent some priests and Levites to him from Jerusalem to ask him, "Who are you?"
B043C001V020	43	1	20	He acknowledged - he did not deny it - but acknowledged, "I am not the Christ."
B043C001V021	43	1	21	"What then?" they questioned; "Are you Elijah?" He said, "I am not."  "Are you the Prophet?" "No," he replied.
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then said they to him. "Who are you? That we may give some answer to those who sent us. What account do you give of yourself?"
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said, "I am a voice of one who cries aloud in the desert, Make straight the way of the Lord, as said the prophet Isaiah."
B043C001V024	43	1	24	Now it was some of the Pharisees who had been sent to him;
B043C001V025	43	1	25	so they questioned him, saying, "Why then are you baptizing, if you are not the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?"
B043C001V026	43	1	26	"I indeed am baptizing in water," John said in reply, "but in your midst stands One whom you do not recognize,
B043C001V027	43	1	27	One who is to come after me, whose sandal-strap I am not worthy to untie."
B043C001V028	43	1	28	This happened in Bethany, beyond Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	The next day he saw Jesus coming toward him, and said. "Behold, that is Gods Lamb, who takes and bears away the sin of the world.
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is he of whom I said, After me comes One who has been put before me, for he was before me.
B043C001V031	43	1	31	I myself did not recognize him; I only came baptizing in water, in order that he might be openly shown to Israel."
B043C001V032	43	1	32	John also bore this testimony, saying. "I saw the Spirit like a dove descend from heaven and rest upon him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	And I did not recognize him, but He who sent me to baptize in water said to me, The one on whom you see the Spirit descending and resting upon him, is he who baptizes in the Holy Spirit.
B043C001V034	43	1	34	This I have seen, and I am become a witness to the fact that he is the Son of God."
B043C001V035	43	1	35	Next day again, John was standing with two of his disciples.
B043C001V036	43	1	36	After gazing intently on Jesus as he walked about, he said, "Look!  that is the Lamb of God!"
B043C001V037	43	1	37	The two disciples heard his exclamation, and they followed Jesus.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	Then Jesus turned and saw them following him, and said, "What do you want?" They replied, "Rabbi" (which may be translated Teacher), "where are you staying?"
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He said to them, "Come, and you shall see." So they went and saw where he was staying, and spent that day with him. It was then about four oclock in the afternoon.
B043C001V040	43	1	40	One of the two men who heard what John said and followed Jesus, was Andrew, the brother of Simon Peter.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	In the morning he found his brother Simon, and said to him, "We have found the Messiah" (a word which means Christ, the Anointed One).
B043C001V042	43	1	42	He brought him to Jesus. Jesus looked intently at him and said. "You are Simon, son of John; you shall be called Cephas" (or Peter,  which means Rock).
B043C001V043	43	1	43	Next day Jesus decided to go into Galilee; and he found Philip and said to him, "Follow me."
B043C001V044	43	1	44	Now Philip belonged to Bethsaida, the same town as Andrew and Peter.
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Then Philip found Nathanael and told him, "We have found him about whom Moses wrote in the Law, as did the prophets - Jesus of Nazareth,  Josephs son."
B043C001V046	43	1	46	And Nathanael said to him, "Can anything good come out of Nazareth?"  Philip said to him, "Come and see."
B043C001V047	43	1	47	Jesus saw Nathanael coming toward him, and said, "Behold a true Israelite in whom there is no deceit."
B043C001V048	43	1	48	"How do you know me?" asked Nathanael. "Before Philip called you,"  replied Jesus, "when you were under the fig tree, I saw you."
B043C001V049	43	1	49	"Rabbi," answered Nathanael, "you are the Son of God; you are King of Israel."
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jesus said in reply. "Do you believe because I said to you, I saw you under the fig tree?
B043C001V051	43	1	51	You shall see greater things than that! Believe me," he added, "you all shall see heaven opened wide, and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the Son of man."
B043C002V001	43	2	1	Now two days after this there was a wedding in Cana of Galilee, and the mother of Jesus was there;
B043C002V002	43	2	2	Jesus also was invited to the wedding, and his disciples.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	And when the wine ran short, Jesus mother said to him, "They have no wine."
B043C002V004	43	2	4	"Woman," said Jesus, "what have you to do with me? My time is not yet come."
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother said to the attendants, "Whatever he may tell you to do,  do it."
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now there were six stone water - jars standing there, according to the Jewish rites of purification, each holding about twenty gallons.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jesus said, "Fill up the jars with water."
B043C002V008	43	2	8	So they filled them brimful. Then he said, "Draw some out now, and carry it to the master of the feast."
B043C002V009	43	2	9	So they carried it. And when the master of the feast had tasted of the water which had been made wine, not knowing where it came from,  though the attendants who had drawn it knew, he called the bridegroom and said to him.
B043C002V010	43	2	10	"Everybody serves first the good wine, and when people have drunk freely, the poor wine; but you have kept the good wine until now."
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This beginning of signs Jesus performed in Cana of Galilee, and showed forth his glory; and his disciples believed on him there.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	Afterward he went down to Capernaum, he and his mother and his brothers and his disciples, and remained there a few days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	Now the Passover of the Jews was near, so Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	There he found in the temple those who were selling cattle and sheep and doves, and the money-changers sitting there.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	So he plaited a scourge of rushes, and drove all out of the temple -  both the sheep and oxen. He began to pour out the coins of the money-  changers, and to overturn their tables,
B043C002V016	43	2	16	and said to those who were selling doves. "Take these things away!  Make not my Fathers house a house of trade!
B043C002V017	43	2	17	His disciples recalled that it is written, The zeal of thine house will devour me.
B043C002V018	43	2	18	Then the Jews asked Jesus, "What sign are you going to show us,  seeing that you do these things?"
B043C002V019	43	2	19	"Destroy this temple," answered Jesus, "and in three days I will raise it up."
B043C002V020	43	2	20	The Jews retorted, "This Temple took forty-six years to build, and will you raise it in three days?"
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But he was speaking about the temple of his body; and when the disciples recalled what he had said,
B043C002V022	43	2	22	after he had been raised from the dead, they believed the Scripture and the word which Jesus had said.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	Now when he was in Jerusalem at the feast of the Passover, many believed in his name, when they beheld the signs which he did;
B043C002V024	43	2	24	but for his part Jesus was not trusting himself to them, because he knew all men,
B043C002V025	43	2	25	and did not need any ones testimony concerning man, for he himself knew what was in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	Now there was one of the Pharisees named Nicodemus, a ruler among the Jews.
B043C003V002	43	3	2	This man came to Jesus by night, and said to him. "Rabbi, we know that you are a teacher sent from God; for no man can do these signs which you are continually doing, unless God is with him."
B043C003V003	43	3	3	"In very truth I tell you," answered Jesus, "that unless a man is born from above, he cannot see the kingdom of God."
B043C003V004	43	3	4	"How can a man be born when he is old?" Nicodemus replied; "Can he enter a second time into his mothers womb, and be born?"
B043C003V005	43	3	5	"I tell you solemnly," Jesus answered, "that unless a man is born of water and the Spirit, he cannot enter the kingdom of God.
B043C003V006	43	3	6	What is born of the flesh is flesh; and what is born of the Spirit is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Marvel not at my telling you, You must all be born again from above.
B043C003V008	43	3	8	The wind blows where it wills, and you hear its voice, but you do not know where it comes from or where it is going. So it is with every one who has been born of the Spirit."
B043C003V009	43	3	9	"How can this be?" said Nicodemus in reply.
B043C003V010	43	3	10	"Are you the Teacher of Israel, and yet you do not understand these things?" said Jesus.
B043C003V011	43	3	11	"Most solemnly I tell you we are speaking of what we know, and it is about that of which we were eyewitnesses that we give testimony. Yet all of you reject our testimony.
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If I have told you earthly things and yet none of you believe me,  how will you believe if I tell you concerning heavenly things?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	There is no one gone up to heaven, except the One who came down from heaven - the Son of man himself.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	And just as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, so must the Son of man be lifted up,
B043C003V015	43	3	15	in order that every one who believes in him may have eternal life.
B043C003V016	43	3	16	"For God so loved the world that he gave his only begotten Son, that whoever trusts in him should not perish, but have eternal life.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For God did not send his Son into the world to condemn the world,  but that the world through him might be saved.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	He who trusts in him is not condemned, but he who does not trust has already been condemned, because he has not put his trust in the name of the only begotten Son of God.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	And this is the condemnation, that Light is come into the world, and men loved darkness rather than light, because their deeds were evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For every one who practises wrong hates light, and does not come to the light, lest his actions be exposed;
B043C003V021	43	3	21	but he who does what is true, comes to the light, in order that his actions may be shown to have been wrought in God."
B043C003V022	43	3	22	After this Jesus and his disciples went into the countryside of Judea, and there he was staying with them and baptizing.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	John also was baptizing in Aenon, near Salim, because there were many streams there, and people kept coming to receive baptism.
B043C003V024	43	3	24	(For John had not yet been thrown into prison.)
B043C003V025	43	3	25	Then some of Johns disciples got into a controversy with a Jew in regard to purification; so they came to John and said to him.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	"Rabbi, see! The man who was with you on the other side of Jordan,  and to whom you yourself have borne testimony, is now baptizing, and everybody is coming to him."
B043C003V027	43	3	27	In reply John said. "A man cannot obtain anything unless it has been granted to him from heaven.
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You yourselves are my witnesses that I said, I am not the Christ,  but have been sent before him.
B043C003V029	43	3	29	He who has the bride is the bridegroom, but the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly because of the bridegrooms voice. So then this joy of mine has now complete fulfilment.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	He must increase, but I must decrease.
B043C003V031	43	3	31	"He that comes from above is above all; but one who is of the earth,  of the earth he is, and of the earth he speaks. He who comes from heaven is above all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	He bears testimony to what he has heard and seen, yet no one receives his testimony.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	Whoever does receive it has set his seal that God is true.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For he whom God sent utters the words of God; for God does not give the Spirit sparingly.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	the Father loves the Son and has committed everything into his hands.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	Whoever believes in the Son has eternal life, but he who disobeys the Son shall not see life, but he who disobeys the Son shall not see life, but the wrath of God abides upon him."
B043C004V001	43	4	1	Accordingly when the Lord knew that the Pharisees had heard it said,  "Jesus is making and baptizing more disciples than John,"
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(though Jesus himself was not accustomed to baptize, but his disciples),
B043C004V003	43	4	3	he left Judea and returned to Galilee.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	Now he had to pass through Samaria;
B043C004V005	43	4	5	so he came to a city of Samaria called Sychar, near the piece of ground that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	Jacobs Spring was there. So Jesus, tired out with his journey, was sitting thus by the spring.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	It was about noon, and a woman of Samaria came to draw water.
B043C004V008	43	4	8	Jesus said to her, "Give me a drink" (for his disciples were gone away into the city to buy food.)
B043C004V009	43	4	9	"How is it," answered the Samaritan woman, "that you who are a Jew ask a drink from me, a woman, and a Samaritan?" (For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.)
B043C004V010	43	4	10	"If you had known the free gift of God," Jesus answered, "and who it is that says to you, Give me a drink, you would have asked of him,  and he would have given you living water."
B043C004V011	43	4	11	"Sir," said the woman, "you have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep; whence have you that living water?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Surely you are not greater than our Father Jacob, who gave us the well, and used to drink from it himself, and his sons, and his cattle, too?"
B043C004V013	43	4	13	"All who drink of this water," Jesus answered, "will thirst again;
B043C004V014	43	4	14	but whoever once drinks of the water that I will give him, shall never thirst any more, but the water that I will give him shall become a living spring of water within him, welling up into eternal life."
B043C004V015	43	4	15	"Sir!" exclaimed the woman, "give me this water, so that I may not be thirsty, nor come all this way to draw water."
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Jesus said to her, "Go, call your husband, and then come here."
B043C004V017	43	4	17	"I have no husband," answered the woman. "You are right in saying I have no husband,"Jesus said to her,
B043C004V018	43	4	18	"for you have had five husbands, and the man you now have is not your husband; in this you have spoken truly."
B043C004V019	43	4	19	"I see, Sir, that you are a prophet," replied the woman.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	"Our forefathers worshiped in this mountain, yet you Jews say that in Jerusalem is the place where one must worship."
B043C004V021	43	4	21	"Woman, believe me," said Jesus, "that the hour is coming when neither in this mountain nor in Jerusalem will you worship the Father.
B043C004V022	43	4	22	You are worshiping something you do not know. we know what we worship, for salvation comes from the Jews.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But an hour is coming, and is now here, when the true worshipers will worship the Father in spirit and in truth. For the Father is seeking such as his worshipers.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	God is spirit, and those who worship him must worship him in spirit and in truth."
B043C004V025	43	4	25	"I know," said the woman, "that Messiah is coming, who is called the Christ; when he has come he will tell us everything."
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jesus said to her, "I who am now talking to you, am he."
B043C004V027	43	4	27	Just then his disciples came up, and were astonished that he was talking with a woman; yet not one of them asked him, "What do you want?" or "Why are you talking with her?"
B043C004V028	43	4	28	Then the woman left her water-jar, and went away into the city and began saying to the people.
B043C004V029	43	4	29	"Come! see a man who has told me everything that I ever did. He cant be the Christ, can he?"
B043C004V030	43	4	30	They left the city and set out to go to him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	Meanwhile the disciples kept urging him.
B043C004V032	43	4	32	"Rabbi," they said, "eat something." But he answered, "I have food to eat of which you know nothing."
B043C004V033	43	4	33	So the disciples began to say to one another, "Can any one have brought him something to eat?"
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jesus said to them. "My food is to do the will of Him who sent me,  and to accomplish his work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Do you not say, It wants yet four months, and then comes the harvest?Look, I tell you! Lift up your eyes and behold the fields,  that they are already white for harvest.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	The reaper is already receiving wages and gathering a crop for eternal life, so that the sower and the reaper may rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	For in this respect the saying is true, One sows, another reaps.
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap a crop on which you have not toiled. Others have toiled, and you have reaped the benefit of their toil."
B043C004V039	43	4	39	Many of the Samaritans of that city believed on him because of the word of the woman when she declared, "He told me everything that I ever did."
B043C004V040	43	4	40	So when the Samaritans arrived, they began asking him to remain with them; and he stayed there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	Then many more believed because of what he said, himself; and they told the woman.
B043C004V042	43	4	42	"We no longer believe because of what you said. for we ourselves have heard him, and we know that this is certainly the Saviour of the world."
B043C004V043	43	4	43	After these two days Jesus went away from there into Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	For Jesus himself testified that a prophet has no honor in his own country.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	When he reached Galilee, however, the Galileans welcomed him, for they had seen all that he did in Jerusalem at the feast; for they,  too, had been at the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	So he came back again to Cana of Galilee, where he made the water wine. Now there was one of the kings officers whose son was lying ill at Capernaum.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	When he heard that Jesus had come from Judea into Galilee, he went to him, and begged him to come down and heal his son who was lying at the point of death.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Then Jesus said to him, "Unless you all see signs and wonders, you will not believe."
B043C004V049	43	4	49	"Sir," said the kings officer, "come down before my little boy dies."
