B043C004V054	43	4	54	This is the second sign which Jesus performed, on returning from Judea to Galilee.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	After this there was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now there is in Jerusalem a pool near the Sheep-gate, called in the Hebrew, Bethesda.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	It has five colonnades. In these there used to lie a great crowd of sick people - blind, lame, paralyzed.
B043C005V005	43	5	5	And there was one man there for thirty-eight years in his infirmity.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	When Jesus saw him lying there, and knew that he had been there a long time, he said to him, "Do you want to get well?"
B043C005V007	43	5	7	"Sir," answered the sick man, "I have no man to put me into the pool whenever the water is troubled; and while I am trying to come, some one else steps down before me."
B043C005V008	43	5	8	"Rise," said Jesus, "take up your bed and go walking away."
B043C005V009	43	5	9	Instantly the man became well, and he took up his bed and started to walk. Now it was Sabbath on that day;
B043C005V010	43	5	10	so the Jews kept saying to the man who had been cured. "It is the Sabbath Day; it is not lawful for you to carry your bed."
B043C005V011	43	5	11	He replied, "The man who healed me told me to take up my bed and walk."
B043C005V012	43	5	12	"Who is it," they asked, "that said to you, take up your bed and go walking away?"
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But he who had been healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had moved away, as there was a crowd in that place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	Afterward Jesus found him in the Temple, and said to him. "Look! You have become well. Do not go on sinning, lest a worse thing befall you."
B043C005V015	43	5	15	The man went to and told the Jews that it was Jesus who made him well;
B043C005V016	43	5	16	and because of this the Jews began to persecute Jesus, because he had done it on the Sabbath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But he answered them, "My Father has continued working until now,  and I am working too."
