B043C005V019	43	5	19	So Jesus answered them in these words. "In solemn truth I tell that the Son cannot do anything of himself, except what he sees the Father doing; for whatever he does, that the Son does also.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	"For the Father loves the Son, and shows him every thing that he himself is doing. And greater deeds than these will he show him, that you may wonder.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	"For just as the Father raises the dead and makes them alive, even so the Son makes whom he will alive.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	"The Father indeed does not judge any one, but has given all judgment to the Son,
B043C005V023	43	5	23	"in order that all may honor the Son even as they honor the Father.  He who does not honor Son, does not honor the Father who sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	"I tell you solemnly that he who listens to my messages and believes Him who sent me, has eternal life. He will not come under condemnation, but has passed out of death into life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	"Solemnly I tell you that the hour is coming, and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God, and those who hear shall live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	"For as the Father has life in himself, so also has he granted to the Son to have life in himself.
B043C005V027	43	5	27	"And he has given him authority to pronounce judgment, because he is Son of man.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	"Do not wonder at this, because an hour is coming in which all who are in their graves shall hear his voice and shall come forth again;
B043C005V029	43	5	29	"those who have done good into a resurrection of life, and those who have practised evil to a resurrection of condemnation.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	"I can of my own self do nothing. As I listen, I judge, and my own judgment is just, because I am not seeking my own will, but the will of Him who sent me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	"If I bear testimony concerning myself, my testimony is not valid.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	"Another bears testimony to me, and I know that the testimony which he bears concerning me is valid.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	"You yourselves sent to John, and he has been and is a witness to the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	"(Though for myself I accept no witness from man; I only mention that you may be saved.)
B043C005V035	43	5	35	"That man was the Lamp-burning and shining - and you were willing for a time rejoice in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	"But I have testimony greater than that of John; for the work which the Father has given me to bring to completion - the work which I am doing - bears testimony concerning me, that the Father has sent me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	"And the Father who sent me has himself borne testimony concerning me. None of you has heard his at any time or seen him,
B043C005V038	43	5	38	nor had his word dwelling within you, because you do not believe him whom he sent.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	"You are searching the Scriptures because you suppose that in tem you have eternal life; and though these are they that bear witness concerning me,
B043C005V040	43	5	40	"you will not come to me that you may have life.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	"I am not receiving honor from men, but I know you,
B043C005V042	43	5	42	"that you have not the love of God in yourselves.
