B043C005V046	43	5	46	"For if you believed Moses you would believe me, for he wrote about me.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	And if you do not believe his writings, how will you ever believe my words?"
B043C006V001	43	6	1	After this Jesus went away across the Sea of Galilee (that is the lake of Tiberias).
B043C006V002	43	6	2	A great crowd were following him, because they witnessed the signs which he was continually performing among those who were ill.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	Then Jesus walked up the hills and sat down there with his disciples. Now the Jewish feast, the Passover, was at hand.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	Accordingly when he looked up, and perceived a great crowd was coming unto him,
B043C006V005	43	6	5	he said to Philip, "Where shall we buy bread for these people to eat?"
B043C006V006	43	6	6	He said this to test him, for he himself knew what he intended to do.
B043C006V007	43	6	7	"Thirty-five dollars worth of bread," answered Philip, "is not enough for them, so that each can take a morsel."
B043C006V008	43	6	8	One of his disciples, Andrew, the brother of Simon, said to him.
