B043C006V015	43	6	15	When Jesus perceived that they intended to seize him in order to make him a king, he retired again to the hill all by himself.
B043C006V016	43	6	16	When evening came on, his disciples went down to the sea.
B043C006V017	43	6	17	There they got in a boat, and started across the sea for Capernaum.  The darkness had already fallen,
B043C006V018	43	6	18	Jesus had not yet come to them, and the sea began to rise, because a strong wind was blowing.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	After they had rowed three or four miles, they saw Jesus walking upon the sea, and drawing near to the boat, and they were terrified;
B043C006V020	43	6	20	but he said to them, "It is I, be not afraid."
B043C006V021	43	6	21	Then they were willing to take him on board, and immediately the boat reached the shore they were making for.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	The crowd that remained on the other side of the sea had seen that there was only one small boat there, and that Jesus had not gone aboard with his disciples, but that his disciples had gone away by themselves.
B043C006V023	43	6	23	So, on the following day, when boats came from Tiberias near the place were they had eaten bread, after the Lord had given thanks,  they got into the boats themselves,
B043C006V024	43	6	24	when they saw that neither Jesus nor his disciples were there, and went to Capernaum to look for Jesus.
B043C006V025	43	6	25	When they found him on the other side of the sea, they said to him,  "Rabbi, when did you get here?"
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jesus answered. "In solemn truth I tell you that you are looking for me, not because you saw miracles signs, but because you ate of the bread and were filled.
B043C006V027	43	6	27	"Labor not for food which perishes, but for the food that endures eternal life - that which the Son of man will give you; for on the Father - God - has set his seal."
B043C006V028	43	6	28	"What are we to do habitually," they asked him, "that we may keep working the words of God?"
B043C006V029	43	6	29	"This is the work of God," answered Jesus, "that you believe on him whom He has sent you."
B043C006V030	43	6	30	The they said to him. "What sign, then, are you performing, so that we may see it and believe in you? What work are you doing?
