B043C017V019	43	17	19	"And for their sakes I dedicate myself, that they also may be thoroughly dedicated in the truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	"Nor do I pray for them alone, but for those also who believe in me through their word,
B043C017V021	43	17	21	"that they may all be one, even as thou, Father, art in me and I in thee; that they also may be in us; in order that the world may believe that thou hast sent me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	"And the glory which thou gavest me I have given them; that they may be one even as we are one,
B043C017V023	43	17	23	"I in them and thou in me; that they may be made perfectly one, so that the world may recognize that thou didst send me, and hast loved them as thou hast loved me.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	"Father, it is my will that wherever I am these also, thy gift to me, may be with me, that they may see the glory, my glory which thou hast given me, because thou didst love me before the foundations of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	"O righteous Father, though the world knew thee not, I have known thee, and these have known that though didst send me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	"And I have declared - and will declare - thy name unto them, that the love with which thou hast loved me may be in them, and that I may be in them."
B043C018V001	43	18	1	After he had spoken these words Jesus went forth with his disciples to a place across the Ravine of the Cedars, where there was a garden into which he and his disciples went.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	Judas the Traitor also knew this place; for Jesus and his disciples often met there.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	So after getting troops and some Temple police from the chief priests and Pharisees, Judas came there with lanterns and torches and weapons.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	Then Jesus, knowing all that was coming upon him, went forth to meet them, and asked them, "Who is it that you are looking for?"
B043C018V005	43	18	5	"For Jesus of Nazareth," they answered. He said to them, "I am he."  (Now Judas also, the betrayer, was standing with them.)
B043C018V006	43	18	6	When Jesus said "I am he," they drew back and fell to the ground;
B043C018V007	43	18	7	so he asked them once more, "Whom are you looking for?" and they replied, "Jesus of Nazareth."
B043C018V008	43	18	8	"I have already told you that I am he," said Jesus. "If, then, you are looking for me, let these go their way."
B043C018V009	43	18	9	"(In order that the word which he had spoken might be fulfilled, "Of those whom thou hast given me I have not lost one.")
B043C018V010	43	18	10	Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it, and striking at the high priests slave, cut off his right ear.
B043C018V011	43	18	11	(The slaves name was Malchus.) Then Jesus said to Peter. "Put up your sword in its sheath. the cup which my Father has given me, shall I not drink it?"
B043C018V012	43	18	12	So the troops and their commandant and the Jewish police took Jesus,  and bound him,
B043C018V013	43	18	13	and led him to Annas first. (For Annas was the Father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was the high priest that year -
B043C018V014	43	18	14	the Caiaphas who had advised the Jews that it was for their advantage that one man should die for the people.)
B043C018V015	43	18	15	Meanwhile Simon Peter was following Jesus, and so was another disciple who was known to the high priest, and they went in with Jesus into the court of the high priests palace.
B043C018V016	43	18	16	But Peter took his stand outside, near the door. So the other disciple who was known to the high priest came out and spoke to the doorkeeper and brought Peter in.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	The doorkeeper (a maid servant) then said to Peter, "Are not you also one of this mans disciples?" "No I am not," he answered.
B043C018V018	43	18	18	Now the slaves and the attendants were standing and warming themselves about a charcoal fire, which they had made because it was cold; and Peter also stood with them, and was warming himself.
B043C018V019	43	18	19	Then the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	Jesus answered him. "I have spoken to all the world openly. I always taught in a synagogue and in the temple, places where all the Jews are wont to assemble, and in secret I have spoken nothing.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	"Why do you question me? Ask those who heard what I have said to them; these witnesses here know what I said."
B043C018V022	43	18	22	When he had spoken these words, one of the police standing by gave him a blow with his hand, saying as he did so, "Is that the way you answer the high priest?"
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus replied "If I have said anything wrong, give evidence concerning the wrong; but if I said what was true, why do you strike me?"
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Then Annas sent him in chains to Caiaphas, the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	Now Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. They said therefore to him, "You are not also one of his disciples, are you not?" He denied it, saying "I am not."
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the slaves of the high priest, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, said, "Did not I myself see you with him in the garden."
B043C018V027	43	18	27	Peter again denied it; and at that very moment a cock crew.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	From the house of Caiaphas they took Jesus to the Praetorium, and it was dawn. They themselves would not enter the Praetorium, in order that they might not be ceremonially defiled, but might be able to eat the Passover.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	So Pilate came outside to them and asked, "What charge do you bring against this man?"
B043C018V030	43	18	30	In reply they said, "If he had not been a criminal, we should not have handed him over you."
B043C018V031	43	18	31	"Take him yourselves," answered Pilate, "and judge him according to your law."
B043C018V032	43	18	32	The Jews answered him, "We are not allowed to put anyone to death"  (that the word of Jesus might be fulfilled in which he predicted the kind of death he was to die).
B043C018V033	43	18	33	So Pilate went into the Praetorium again, and summoned Jesus. "Are you the King of the Jews?" he said.
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus answered, "Are you saying this of your own accord, or did others say it to you about me?"
B043C018V035	43	18	35	"I am not a Jew, am I?" replied Pilate; "It is your own nation and the high priests who have handed you over to me. What have you done?"
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus answered him. "My kingdom is not of this world. If my kingdom were of this world, then would my servants have fought hard that I should not be handed the Jews; but in reality my kingdom is not of such origins."
B043C018V037	43	18	37	"You are a king, then? You!" said Pilate. "You say truly that I am a king." answered Jesus, "for this purpose I was born, and to this end came I into the world, that I should bear witness to the truth. Every man who is of the truth listens to my voice."
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to him, "What is truth?" As he said this, he went outside again to the Jews and said to them.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	"I find no crime in this man. Now it is a custom of yours that I release one prisoner to you at the time of the Passover feast. Do you wish me to release to you the King of the Jews?"
B043C018V040	43	18	40	Then they all shouted again. "No, not him! Barabbas!" Now Barabbas was a robber.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	After that Pilate took Jesus and had him scourged;
B043C019V002	43	19	2	and the soldiers plaited a crown of thorns, placed it on his head,  and threw a purple cloak about him, and kept marching up to him,
B043C019V003	43	19	3	saying, "Hail! King of the Jews!" They also gave him blow after blow with their hands.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	Pilate again came forth and said to the people, "See, I am going to bring his out to you, that you may clearly know that I find no crime in him,"
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Then as Jesus came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe, Pilate said to them, "BEHOLD, THE MAN!"
B043C019V006	43	19	6	So when the chief priests and the police saw him, they shouted.  "Crucify him! Crucify him!" "Take him yourselves and crucify him,"  said Pilate, "for I find no crime in him."
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jews answered him, "We have a law, and by that law he ought to die, because he made himself out to be Gods Son,"
B043C019V008	43	19	8	Now when Pilate heard these words he was more alarmed than ever,
B043C019V009	43	19	9	and entering the Praetorium again, he said to Jesus, "What is your origin?"
B043C019V010	43	19	10	Jesus made no answer. So Pilate said to him. "Do you not speak to me? Do you not know that I have power to release you, or power to crucify you?"
B043C019V011	43	19	11	"You would have no power over me," answered Jesus, "unless it had been given you from above. For this reason he who has betrayed me to you has the greater sin."
B043C019V012	43	19	12	After that Pilate began to seek to release him, but the Jews shouted out. "If you release this man you are no friend of the Emperor. Any man who makes himself out to be king is a rebel against the Emperor."
B043C019V013	43	19	13	On hearing what they said, Pilate brought Jesus out and made him sit on the judges seat in a place called the Mosaic Pavement (the Hebrew name is Gabbatha).
B043C019V014	43	19	14	And it was the day of Preparation for the Passover, about six oclock in the morning. Then he said to the Jews, "Behold your King!"
B043C019V015	43	19	15	Then they shouted. "Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!"  "Crucify your King?" said Pilate. The chief priests answered, "We have no king but Caesar!"
B043C019V016	43	19	16	So then he gave him over to them to be crucified.
B043C019V017	43	19	17	So they took Jesus, who went forth bearing his own cross, to a place called The Place of a Skull - in the Hebrew tongue, Golgotha.
B043C019V018	43	19	18	There they crucified him; and with him two others, one on either side, and Jesus between them.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	And Pilate moreover wrote an inscription and placed it above the cross. What he wrote was, "JESUS, THE NAZARENE, KING OF THE JEWS"
B043C019V020	43	19	20	This inscription was read by many of the Jews, because the place where they crucified Jesus was near the city, and the inscription was written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	So the high priests of the Jews said to Pilate, "Do not write King of the Jews, but He said, I am King of the Jews."
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilate answered, "What I have written, I have written!"
B043C019V023	43	19	23	After the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they took his garments and divided them into four parts, to each soldier a part, and the tunic.  Now the tunic was seamless, woven in one piece from top to bottom;
B043C019V024	43	19	24	so the soldiers said one to another. "Let us not tear it. Let us draw lots, to see whose it shall be" - that the Scripture might be fulfilled. They divided my garments among them, For my raiment did they cast lots. This was what the soldiers did.
B043C019V025	43	19	25	Now there stood near the cross of Jesus, his mother and his mothers sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	When Jesus saw his mother, and standing near her the disciple whom he loved, he said to his mother, "Woman behold your son."
B043C019V027	43	19	27	Then he said to the disciple, "Behold your mother." And from that hour the disciple took her to his home.
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After that, when Jesus knew that everything was now accomplished, he said in fulfilment of the words of Scripture, "I am thirsty."
B043C019V029	43	19	29	There was a jar full of vinegar standing there; and they filled a sponge with vinegar, and put it upon a stalk of hyssop, and put it to his lips.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	Then after he had taken the vinegar, Jesus said, "IT IS FINISHED!"  And bowing his head, he yielded up his spirit.
B043C019V031	43	19	31	It was Preparation Day, so in order to prevent the bodies hanging on the cross during the Sabbath (for the Sabbath was a great day) the Jews begged Pilate to have the legs broken, and the bodies taken away.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the first man and of the other who had been crucified with him.
B043C019V033	43	19	33	But upon coming to Jesus they saw that he was already dead, and did not break his legs.
B043C019V034	43	19	34	One of the soldiers, however, pierced his side with a lance, and immediately blood and water flowed out.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	And he who saw it has borne testimony, and his testimony is trustworthy, and he knows that he is telling the truth in order that you may believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For this happened that the Scripture might be fulfilled, Not one of his bones shall be broken.
B043C019V037	43	19	37	And again another Scripture says, They shall look on him whom they have pierced.
B043C019V038	43	19	38	After these things Joseph of Arimathea, who was a disciple of Jesus,  but in secret because of fear of the Jews, asked Pilate for permission to take the body of Jesus, and Pilate gave him leave. So he came and took the body.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	Nicodemus also (the one who visited Jesus by night, at first) came bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes, weighing nearly a hundred pounds.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	So they took the body of Jesus and wound it in linen with the spices, according to the Jewish mode of burial.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	There was a garden near the place where Jesus had been crucified,  and in the garden a new tomb in which no one had ever been laid.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	Here, because of its being Preparation Day, and as the tomb was near by, they placed Jesus.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	On the first day of the week, very early in the morning, while it was yet dark, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb and discovered that the stone had been removed from the tomb.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	So she came running to Simon Peter and that other disciple whom Jesus loved, saying, "They have taken the Master out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him!"
B043C020V003	43	20	3	So Peter and the other disciples set out at once to go to the tomb.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	They both began to run; and the other disciple ran faster than Peter, and came first to the tomb.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	Stooping down he glanced in and saw the linen wrapping lying on the ground; but he did not go in.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	Then Peter also came following him, and he went inside the tomb; and he gazed at the linen wrapping as they lay,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	and the napkin which had been about his head not lying with the wrappings, but rolled up in its own place.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	Then the other disciple also who arrived first at the tomb went inside, and he perceived and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	For not yet had they understood the Scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.
B043C020V010	43	20	10	Then the disciples went back again to their home.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	Meanwhile, outside, Mary stood sobbing near the tomb. Still sobbing she stooped and looked into the tomb,
B043C020V012	43	20	12	and gazed at two angels in glistening white sitting, one at the head the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	They said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping?" She answered,  "Because they have taken away my Master, and I do not know where they have laid him."
B043C020V014	43	20	14	When she had said this she turned around and saw Jesus standing there, but did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her. "Woman, why are you weeping? Whom are you seeking? She, supposing that he was the gardener, said to him, "Sir,  if you have borne him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will take him away, myself."
B043C020V016	43	20	16	"Mary," said Jesus. She turned to him. "Rabboni!" she cried in Hebrew. That is to say, "Teacher."
B043C020V017	43	20	17	"Do not cling to me," said Jesus, "for I am not yet ascended to the Father. But go to my brothers and say to them, "I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God."
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Away went Mary Magdalene to the disciples with the tidings, "I have seen the Master!" and that he said these things to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	On the evening of that same day, the first day of the week, although the doors of the room where the disciples gathered had been locked for fear of the Jews, Jesus came, and there he stood among them,  saying. "Peace to you!"
B043C020V020	43	20	20	As he said this he showed them his hands and his side. Then were the disciple glad, when they saw the Lord.
B043C020V021	43	20	21	Then Jesus said to them again. "Peace to you. As my Father has sent me forth, I also now am sending you."
B043C020V022	43	20	22	When he had said this he breathed upon them and said.
B043C020V023	43	20	23	"Receive the Holy Spirit. If you remit any ones sins, they are remitted; if you retain them they are retained."
B043C020V024	43	20	24	But Thomas, one of the Twelve, who was called "The Twin." was not with them when Jesus came.
B043C020V025	43	20	25	Accordingly the other disciples kept telling him, "We have seen the Lord." But he told them, "Unless I see in his hands the print of the nails, and thrust my finger into the print of the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe it."
B043C020V026	43	20	26	A week later his disciples were again in the house, and Thomas was with them. Jesus came, although the doors were locked, and stood there among and said. "Peace to you!"
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then to Thomas he said. "Place your finger here, and see my hands;  and place your hand here, and thrust it into my side, and become not unbelieving, but believing."
B043C020V028	43	20	28	Thomas answered him, "My Lord and my God!"
B043C020V029	43	20	29	"Because you have seen me, Thomas, you have believed," Jesus told him. "Blessed are those who, without seeing, yet believed."
B043C020V030	43	20	30	There were then many other signs which Jesus performed in the presence of his disciples, which have not been written in this book;
B043C020V031	43	20	31	but these have been written that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life in his name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	After this Jesus showed himself again to his disciples by the Sea of Tiberias. He showed himself as follows.
B043C021V002	43	21	2	There were together Simon Peter and Thomas, called "The Twin," and Nathanael, from Cana of Galilee, and the two sons of Zebedee, and two others of his disciples.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, "I am going fishing." They answered him,  "And we are going with you." So they went out and got into the boat,  and throughout the night they caught nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	But when day was dawning Jesus stood on the beach. The disciples,  however, did not recognize that it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	So Jesus said to them, "Lads, you havent any fish, have you?" They answered him, "No."
B043C021V006	43	21	6	And he said to them, "Cast your net on the right side of the boat,  and you will find." So they cast it, and now they could not haul it in for the multitude of fishes.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	Then that disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It is the Lord!"  On hearing that it was the Lord, Simon Peter girt his fishers coat about him (for he was naked), and threw himself into the water.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	The rest of the disciples came in the boat, for they were not far from shore - only about a hundred yards - dragging in the net full of fish.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	When they got to the shore they beheld a charcoal fire ready laid,  with fish on it, and some bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	"Bring some of the fish you have just caught," Jesus told them.
B043C021V011	43	21	11	So Simon Peter went and dragged the net to shore, full of large fish, a hundred and fifty-three of them; but for all this number the net was not torn.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	"Come and have breakfast," said Jesus to them. Not one of the disciples dared ask him, "Who are you?" Knowing that it was the Lord.
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Jesus went and took bread and gave it to them, and the fish also.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This was the third time that Jesus showed himself to the disciples after he had risen from among the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	When they were through breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon,  son of John, do you love me more than these others do?" "Yes, Lord,  you know that you are dear to me." he answered. Jesus said to him,  "Feed my lambs."
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He said to him a second time, "Simon, son of John, do you love me?"  He answered, "Yes, Lord, you know that you are dear to me." "Be a shepherd to my sheep," said Jesus.
B043C021V017	43	21	17	The third time Jesus asked him, "Am I really dear to you?" Peter was grieved because the third time he asked, "Am I really dear to you?"  and he answered, "Master, you know all things, you know that you are dear to me."
B043C021V018	43	21	18	"Feed my sheep," said Jesus. "In solemn truth I tell you that when you were young, you used to put on your own girdle, and walk wherever you wished; but when you grow old you will stretch out your hands for some one to gird you, and carry you where you do not wish to go."
B043C021V019	43	21	19	This he said to show by what kind of death Peter was to glorify God.  After speaking thus, he said to him, "Follow me."
B043C021V020	43	21	20	Peter turned around and saw that the disciple whom Jesus loved was following - he who at the supper leaned back upon his breast and said,  "Lord, who is to betray you?"
B043C021V021	43	21	21	On catching sight of him, Peter said to Jesus, "Lord, what about him?"
B043C021V022	43	21	22	"If I choose that he remain until I come," said Jesus, "what is that to you? Do you follow me."
B043C021V023	43	21	23	Accordingly the report spread among the brothers that this disciple should not die; but Jesus did not say that he was not to die, but said, "If I choose that he remain until I come, what is that to you?"
B043C021V024	43	21	24	It is this disciple who bears testimony to these facts and who recorded them; and we know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	But there are also many other things which Jesus did; if every one of them were to be recorded in detail I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that would have to be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	My first account, O Theophilus, dealt with all that Jesus began doing and teaching from the beginning down to the day when,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	after giving instructions through the Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen, he was taken up to heaven.
B044C001V003	44	1	3	After his sufferings he had also shown himself alive to them in many convincing manifestations, revealing himself to them during forty days, and speaking of the kingdom of God.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And once when he was eating with them he charged them not to depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father. "Of this,"  he said, "you have heard from me.
B044C001V005	44	1	5	"For John indeed baptized in water, but you shall be baptized in the Holy Spirit not many days hence."
B044C001V006	44	1	6	So, when they came together, they began to ask him, "Master, are you at this time about to restore the kingdom of Israel?"
B044C001V007	44	1	7	He answered. "It is not for you to know times and occasions which the Father has fixed in his own authority;
B044C001V008	44	1	8	"yet you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes upon you, and you are to be my witnesses both in Jerusalem and in all Judea, and in Samaria, and to the very ends of the earth."
B044C001V009	44	1	9	When he had said this, and while they were looking at him, he was lifted up, and a cloud received him up out of their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	While they were gazing into the sky as he was going up, suddenly there were two men in white garments standing by them,
B044C001V011	44	1	11	and they said. "Men of Galilee, why do you stand gazing into the sky? This same Jesus who has been taken up from you into the sky will come back in just the same way as you have seen him going into the sky."
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mountain called Olivet,  which is near Jerusalem, about a Sabbath Days journey distant.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	On entering the city they went to the upper room where they were accustomed to meet. They were Peter and John and James and Andrew,  Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James, son of Alphaeus,  and Simon the Zealot, and Judas the son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	These all with one mind gave their constant attention to prayer,  together with some women, and with Mary the mother of Jesus, and his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	It was during these days that Peter stood up among the brothers - the whole number of persons present was about one hundred and twenty - and said.
B044C001V016	44	1	16	"Men and brothers, it was necessary for the Scripture to be fulfilled which the Holy Spirit uttered beforehand by the lips of David in regard to Judas who acted as guide to those who arrested Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	"For he was numbered among us, and he did get his allotted share of this ministry.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	"Now this man bought a plot of ground with the price of his treachery, and falling there headlong he burst asunder and all his bowels gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	"This fact became known to the people of Jerusalem so that the place was called in their language, Acheldamach, The Field of Blood.
B044C001V020	44	1	20	"For it is written in the Book of Psalms, Let his dwelling-place be desolate; Let no man dwell there, also, Let another take his work.
B044C001V021	44	1	21	"It is necessary then that, of the men who have been associated with us during the whole time in which the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	from his baptism by John down to the day on which he was taken up from us, one should join us a witness to his resurrection."
B044C001V023	44	1	23	So they placed two in nomination, Joseph called Bar-Sabbas (surnamed Justas) and Matthias;
B044C001V024	44	1	24	and they prayed, saying. "Thou, O Lord, who knowest the hearts of all men, show clearly which of these two men thou hast chosen to fill the place
B044C001V025	44	1	25	"in this ministry of this apostles from which Judas went out to go to his own place."
B044C001V026	44	1	26	Then they cast lots for them, and the lot fell upon Matthias, and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	When the day of Pentecost was fully come, and they were all together in the same place,
B044C002V002	44	2	2	there came suddenly from the sky a sound like the onrush of a mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	There appeared to them tongues, like flame, distributing themselves,  one resting upon the head of each one,
B044C002V004	44	2	4	and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other tongues as the Spirit was giving them utterance.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	Now there were, staying in Jerusalem. devout Jews from many and distant lands.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	So when this noise was heard, the crowd gathered in bewilderment because each man heard them speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	The were beside themselves with wonder. "Are not these Galileans who are speaking?" they exclaimed.
B044C002V008	44	2	8	"Then how is it that each one of us hears them speak his own mother tongue?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians, Medes, Elamites, dwellers in Mesopotamia, in Judea, in Cappadocia, in Pontus and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	in Phrygia, Pamphylia, Egypt, and the district of Lybia around Cretans and Arabians,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	we all hear these men telling in our own tongue what great things God has done."
B044C002V012	44	2	12	All were astonished and bewildered and kept saying to one another,  "What can this mean?"
B044C002V013	44	2	13	But others were saying with jeer, "These men are full of sweet wine."
B044C002V014	44	2	14	Then Peter, with the Eleven, stood up and addresses them in a loud voice. "Men of Judea and dwellers in Jerusalem, have no doubt about this matter, but listen to what I say.
B044C002V015	44	2	15	"These men are not drunk, as you suppose, since it is only nine oclock in the morning.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	"No, this is what the prophet Joel predicted.
B044C002V017	44	2	17	"In the last days, God says, it shall come to pass that I will pour out my Spirit upon all mankind; "Your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, your young men shall see visions, your old men shall dream dreams;
B044C002V018	44	2	18	upon my slaves, both men and women, in those days, will I pour out my Spirit, and they shall prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	In the sky above I will show marvels, And signs in the earth beneath; Blood and fire, and vapor of smoke.
B044C002V020	44	2	20	Into darkness shall the sun be turned, And into blood the moon, Ere the day of the Lord come, that great and terrible day.
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And every one who calls upon the name of the Lord will be saved.
B044C002V022	44	2	22	"Men of Israel, listen to these words. Jesus the Nazarene, a man accredited to you by God, through mighty works and wonders and signs which God did by him among you, as you yourselves know;
B044C002V023	44	2	23	him, delivered up by the settled purpose and fore-knowledge of God,  you crucified and killed at the hands of lawless men;
B044C002V024	44	2	24	but God has raised him to life, having loosed the pangs of death,  because it was not possible for death to hold him.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David says of him. "I beheld the Lord always before my face; For he is at my right hand lest I be shaken.
B044C002V026	44	2	26	"Therefore my heart is glad, my tongue exults, my very body also shall pitch its tent in hope.
B044C002V027	44	2	27	"For thou wilt not leave my soul in Hades, Nor give up thy Holy One to see corruption.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	"Thou hast made known to me the paths of life, Thou wilt fill me with gladness in thy presence.
B044C002V029	44	2	29	"Men and brothers, I can speak plainly to you concerning the patriarch David, because he not only died and was buried, but his tomb is among us even to this very day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	"Because he was a prophet and knew that God had sworn to him with an oath that of the fruit of his loins he would set one on his throne,
B044C002V031	44	2	31	"he, foreseeing this, spoke of the resurrection of Christ that neither was he left in Hades, nor did his flesh see corruption.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jesus God has raised up, of this we are all witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	Since he is by the mighty hand of God exalted, and has received from his Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured forth this which you now see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David did not ascend into heaven; but he himself said, "The Lord said to my Lord Sit thou on my right hand
B044C002V035	44	2	35	"Until I make thine enemies A footstool under thy feet.
B044C002V036	44	2	36	"Therefore let the whole House of Israel know assuredly that Gods has made him both Lord and Christ, this Jesus whom you have crucified."
B044C002V037	44	2	37	When they heard these words they were stung to the heart, and said to Peter and the rest of the apostles. "Men and brothers, what shall we do?"
B044C002V038	44	2	38	"Repent," answered Peter, "and be baptized, every one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ, for the remission of your sins, and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	"For the promise belongs to you and to your children and to all who are afar off, whomever the Lord may call."
