B044C007V020	44	7	20	"In this time Moses was born, a divinely beautiful child, who was brought up for three months in his fathers house.
B044C007V021	44	7	21	"When he was exposed, Pharaohs daughter took him up, and brought him up as her own son.
B044C007V022	44	7	22	"So Moses was educated in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in his words and works.
B044C007V023	44	7	23	"And when he was forty years old it came into his heart to visit his brothers, the children of Israel;
B044C007V024	44	7	24	"and when he saw one of them wronged he wrought redress for the one overpowered, by striking down the Egyptian.
B044C007V025	44	7	25	"(Now he supposed that his brothers would understand how God by his hand was bringing them deliverance; but they did not.)
B044C007V026	44	7	26	"Next day he came upon two of them fighting, and tried to make peace between them. "Sirs, he said, you are brothers. Why are you wronging each other?
B044C007V027	44	7	27	"But the man who was ill-treating his neighbor thrust him aside,  saying, "Who made you a magistrate and ruler over us?
B044C007V028	44	7	28	"Do you want to kill me, as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?
B044C007V029	44	7	29	"Alarmed at this question, Moses fled from the land, and went to live in the land of Midian. There he became the father of two sons.
B044C007V030	44	7	30	"But at the end of forty years there appeared to him, in the desert of Mt. Sinai, an angel in a flame of fire, in a bush.
B044C007V031	44	7	31	"When Moses saw it he was astonished at the sight. But when he drew near to look, the voice of the Lord said,
B044C007V032	44	7	32	"I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.  "And Moses trembled and dared not gaze.
B044C007V033	44	7	33	"And the Lord said. "Take off your sandals, for the place on which you are standing is holy ground.
B044C007V034	44	7	34	"Truly I have seen the oppression of my people in Egypt, and I have heard their groans, and am come down to rescue them; and now, come, I will send you into Egypt.
B044C007V035	44	7	35	"This Moses whom they refused when they said, Who made you to be a ruler and a judge? that same Moses we find God sending as a ruler and a redeemer by the hand in the bush.
B044C007V036	44	7	36	"This was he who brought them out, after he had shown signs and wonders in the wilderness, for forty years.
B044C007V037	44	7	37	"It was this Moses who said to the Children of Israel, "God will raise up a Prophet for you from among your brothers, as he did me.
B044C007V038	44	7	38	"This is the one who was in the congregation in the wilderness along with the angel who spoke to him in Mt. Sinai, and with our ancestors to whom he gave living words to hand down to us.
B044C007V039	44	7	39	"To him our ancestors would not be obedient, but thrust him aside,  and in their hearts turned back into Egypt.
B044C007V040	44	7	40	"Said they to Aaron. "Make Gods for us who shall march in front of us! As for this Moses who led us forth out of the land of Egypt, we know not what has happened to him.
B044C007V041	44	7	41	"And they made a calf in those days, and offered a sacrifice to this idol, and began to rejoice over what they had made with their hands.
B044C007V042	44	7	42	"So God turned from them, and gave them up to the worship of the heavenly host, as it is written in the book of the Prophets. "Did you offer unto me slain beasts as sacrifices during the forty years in the wilderness, O House of Israel?
B044C007V043	44	7	43	No, it was the Tabernacle of Moloch and the star-symbol of the god Rempha that you lifted up - the images which you made in order to worship them; so I will carry you away beyond Babylon.
B044C007V044	44	7	44	"In the wilderness our ancestors had the Tabernacle of Testimony built, as he appointed who told Moses to make it according to the pattern he had seen.
B044C007V045	44	7	45	"That tabernacle was brought in by our ancestors, in their turn,  when they under Joshua entered on the possession of the nations whom God thrust out before them, until the days of David.
B044C007V046	44	7	46	"David obtained favor with God, and asked permission to find a dwelling-place for the God of Jacob.
B044C007V047	44	7	47	"But it was Solomon who built him a house.
B044C007V048	44	7	48	"Yet the Most High does not dwell in houses made with hands; as said the prophet.
B044C007V049	44	7	49	"The heaven is my throne, And the earth the footstool of my feet;  What kind of house will you build for me? saith the Lord. Or what resting-place shall I have?
B044C007V050	44	7	50	Did not my hand make this universe?
B044C007V051	44	7	51	"Stiff-necked, uncircumcised in heart and ears! You are always resisting the Holy Ghost! As your fathers did, so do you.
B044C007V052	44	7	52	"Which of the prophets did not your fathers persecute? They killed those who foretold the coming of the Righteous One, whose betrayers and murderers you have now become -
B044C007V053	44	7	53	"you who received the law, given through angels, and obeyed it not."
B044C007V054	44	7	54	As they heard these words they became furious and gnashed their teeth at him.
B044C007V055	44	7	55	But he, full of the Holy Spirit, looked up stedfastly into heaven,  and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing at the right hand of God.
B044C007V056	44	7	56	"Look, I see heaven open," he said, "And the Son of man standing at the right hand of God."
B044C007V057	44	7	57	With a loud outcry they stopped their ears, and rushed upon Stephen in a body,
B044C007V058	44	7	58	dragged him outside the city, and stoned him, the witnesses throwing off their outer garments at the feet of a young man named Saul.
B044C007V059	44	7	59	So they stoned Stephen while he prayed, "Lord Jesus, receive my spirit."
B044C007V060	44	7	60	Then he knelt down and cried aloud, "Lord, lay not this sin to their charge."
B044C008V001	44	8	1	With these words he fell asleep. And Saul fully approved of his murder. On this very day there broke out a great persecution against the church in Jerusalem, and all except the apostle were scattered throughout Judea and Samaria.
B044C008V002	44	8	2	Devout men buried Stephen, and made loud lamentations over him.
B044C008V003	44	8	3	But Saul was laying waste the church. He was wont to enter into every house, and to drag off men and women, and to commit them to prison.
B044C008V004	44	8	4	So those who were scattered abroad were going everywhere preaching the word.
B044C008V005	44	8	5	Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and began to preach Christ there.
B044C008V006	44	8	6	The crowd with one accord were giving heed to what he said, when they heard and saw the signs that he did.
B044C008V007	44	8	7	For with a loud cry unclean spirits would come out of many possessed by them, and many that were palsied and lame were healed.
B044C008V008	44	8	8	There began to be great joy in that city.
B044C008V009	44	8	9	Now for some time a man named Simon had been practising sorcery in that city, and had amazed the people of Samaria. He gave himself out to be some great person.
B044C008V010	44	8	10	Many from all classes would give heed to him, declaring, "This man is the Power of God, known as the Great Power."
B044C008V011	44	8	11	They were giving heed to him because, for a long time, he had amazed them with his sorceries.
B044C008V012	44	8	12	But when they believed Philip, who was preaching glad tidings about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they began to be baptized, both men and women.
B044C008V013	44	8	13	And Simon himself also believed, and after his baptism he remained with Philip, and was full of amazement as he beheld the signs and striking miracles which were performed.
B044C008V014	44	8	14	The apostle at Jerusalem, when they heard that Samaria had accepted the word of God, sent to them Peter and John.
B044C008V015	44	8	15	Who came down and prayed for them, that they might receive the Holy Spirit,
B044C008V016	44	8	16	For he had not yet fallen upon any of them; they had simply been baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C008V017	44	8	17	Then the apostles laid their hands upon them, and they received the Holy Spirit.
B044C008V018	44	8	18	But when Simon perceived that, by the laying on of the apostles  hands, the Spirit was given, he offered them money saying,
B044C008V019	44	8	19	"Give me, too, this power, so that on whomever I lay my hands, he may receive the Holy Spirit."
B044C008V020	44	8	20	But Peter said to him. "Your money perish with you, because you have supposed that with money you can obtain Gods free gift!"
B044C008V021	44	8	21	"You have no part or lot in this matter." Your heart is not right in the sight of God.
B044C008V022	44	8	22	Repent then of this your wickedness, and beseech the Lord to forgive you this purpose of your heart.
B044C008V023	44	8	23	"For I perceive that you still stand in the gall of bitterness and in the bondage of unrighteousness."
B044C008V024	44	8	24	And Simon answered, "Pray to the Lord for me, both of you, that nothing which you have said may happen to me."
B044C008V025	44	8	25	So the apostles, after bearing solemn witness, and declaring the message of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, evangelizing many Samaritan villages as they went.
B044C008V026	44	8	26	And an angel of the Lord spoke to Philip, saying, "Arise and go on your way south, along the road that runs down from Jerusalem to Gaza,  the desert way."
B044C008V027	44	8	27	So he arose and went. And behold an Ethiopian man, a eunuch, who was a high official (a chief treasurer) of Candace, the queen of Ethiopia, who had come to Jerusalem to worship
B044C008V028	44	8	28	Was now on his way home, and was reading the Prophet Isaiah as he sat in his chariot.
B044C008V029	44	8	29	And the Spirit said to Philip, "Go up and join that chariot."
B044C008V030	44	8	30	So Philip ran up, and heard him reading Isaiah the Prophet, and said to him. "Do you understand what you are reading?"
B044C008V031	44	8	31	The eunuch answered, "Why, how can I unless someone shall show me the way?" And he begged Philip to get up and sit with him.
B044C008V032	44	8	32	Now the portion of Scripture which he was reading was as follows. He was led a sheep to the slaughter; And as a lamb before its shearer is dumb, So he opened not his mouth.
B044C008V033	44	8	33	In his humiliation justice was denied him. Who will declare his posterity? For his life is cut off from the earth.
B044C008V034	44	8	34	"Pray," asked the eunuch of Philip, "of whom is the prophet speaking? Of himself, or of some one else?"
B044C008V035	44	8	35	Then Philip opened his lips, and beginning from that same scripture,  he preached the gospel of Jesus to him.
B044C008V036	44	8	36	And as they were going on their way they came to a certain water,  and the eunuch said. "See, here is water! What hinders my being baptized?"
B044C008V037	44	8	37	And Philip said, "If you believe with your whole heart, you may."  The eunuch answered, "I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God."
B044C008V038	44	8	38	And he ordered the chariot to stop; and both of them, Philip and the eunuch, went down into the water, and Philip baptized him.
B044C008V039	44	8	39	And when they had come up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord snatched Philip away, and the eunuch saw him no more, but continued on his way rejoicing.
B044C008V040	44	8	40	Philip found himself at Ashdod. Then visiting town after town, he kept preaching the good news in all the cities until he reached Caesarea.
B044C009V001	44	9	1	Meanwhile Saul, still breathing out threats of murder against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest
B044C009V002	44	9	2	and begged of him letters addressed to the synagogues in Damascus,  so that if he found any that were of the Way, either men or women, he could bind them and bring them to Jerusalem.
B044C009V003	44	9	3	And as he journeyed, when he was approaching Damascus, suddenly a light from heaven flashed round him.
B044C009V004	44	9	4	He fell to the ground, and heard a voice which said to him, "Saul,  Saul, why are you persecuting me?"
B044C009V005	44	9	5	And he said, "Who are you Lord?"
B044C009V006	44	9	6	"I am Jesus, whom you are persecuting," he said. "Stand up and go into the city, and there you shall be told what you must do."
B044C009V007	44	9	7	Meanwhile the men who were his fellow travelers stood speechless,  hearing indeed the voice, but beholding no one.
B044C009V008	44	9	8	And Saul got up from the ground, but although his eyes were open, he continued to perceive nothing; so they took him by the hand and led him into Damascus.
B044C009V009	44	9	9	And he remained there three days, seeing nothing, and without eating or drinking.
B044C009V010	44	9	10	Now there was in Damascus a disciple named Ananias, and the Lord spoke to him in a vision, saying, "Ananias!" And he answered, "Lo, I am here, Lord."
B044C009V011	44	9	11	And the Lord said to him. "Arise, go into the street named Straight, and make inquiries in the house of Judas for a man of Tarsus, one Saul.
B044C009V012	44	9	12	He is now praying, and has seen a man named Ananias enter and lay his hands on him to restore his sight."
B044C009V013	44	9	13	"But, Lord," said Ananias, "I have heard from many about that man,  and how much evil he did to the saints at Jerusalem!
B044C009V014	44	9	14	"In this city, too, he has authority from the chief priests to arrest all those who call upon thy name."
B044C009V015	44	9	15	"Go," answered the Lord, "this man is chosen instrument of mine to bear my name before the nations and their kings, and before the Children of Israel also;
B044C009V016	44	9	16	"for I am going to show him all he has to suffer for the sake of my name."
B044C009V017	44	9	17	And so Ananias went and entered into the house, and laying his hands on him, said, "Brother Saul, the Lord, even Jesus, who appeared to you on your journey, has sent me that you may receive your sight, and be filled with the Holy Spirit."
B044C009V018	44	9	18	Instantly something like scales fell from his eyes, and he received his sight. He arose and was baptized.
B044C009V019	44	9	19	Afterward he took food and was strengthened. And he remained for some time with the disciples at Damascus.
B044C009V020	44	9	20	And he began at once to proclaim in the synagogues Jesus as the Son of God.
B044C009V021	44	9	21	His hearers were all astonished, and began to say. "Is not this the very man who in Jerusalem made havoc of those who called upon the Name? Did he not come hither for the express purpose of carrying them all in chains to the high priests?"
