B044C009V030	44	9	30	When they learned this the brothers took him down to Caesarea, and then sent him forth to Tarsus.
B044C009V031	44	9	31	Now throughout the whole of Judea, Galilee, and Samaria the Church continued to enjoy peace and to be spiritually built up. It was increasing in members also, as it kept walking in the fear of the Lord, and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit.
B044C009V032	44	9	32	Now Peter, as he was going from town to town, came down also to the saints who lived in Lydda.
B044C009V033	44	9	33	Here he found a man named Aeneas, bedridden for eight years, a paralytic.
B044C009V034	44	9	34	Peter said to him. "Aeneas, Jesus Christ cures you! Rise and make your own bed!"
B044C009V035	44	9	35	At once he rose to his feet. All the people of Lydda and Sharon saw him, and they turned to the Lord.
