B044C009V043	44	9	43	Peter stayed for some time in Joppa, lodging in the house of Simon,  the tanner.
B044C010V001	44	10	1	Now there was at Caesarea a man named Cornelius, a captain in the Italian regiment.
B044C010V002	44	10	2	He was a devout man and God-fearing, and so were all his household.  He gave many alms to the people, and constantly prayed to God.
B044C010V003	44	10	3	About three oclock one afternoon he had a vision, and distinctly saw an angel of God enter his house and say to him, "Cornelius."
B044C010V004	44	10	4	He stared at him in terror, and said, "What is it, Lord?" "Your prayers and your alms have risen for a memorial before God," answered the angel;
B044C010V005	44	10	5	"and now send men to Joppa and fetch one Simon, who is called Peter.
B044C010V006	44	10	6	"He is staying as a guest with Simon, a tanner, whose house is near the sea."
B044C010V007	44	10	7	And after the angel who was speaking to him was gone, he called two of his household servants and a devout soldier who was in constant attendance upon him,
B044C010V008	44	10	8	and after telling them everything, he sent them to Joppa.
B044C010V009	44	10	9	The next day, while they were still on their way and were approaching the town, about noon, Peter went up to the housetop to pray.
B044C010V010	44	10	10	He had become very hungry and longed for food; but while they were preparing it, he fell into a trance.
B044C010V011	44	10	11	He beheld the sky opened, and a vessel descending like an enormous sail let down to earth by four corners.
B044C010V012	44	10	12	In it were all kinds of quadrupeds and creeping things of the earth,  and wild birds.
B044C010V013	44	10	13	A voice came to him, saying, "Rise, Peter, kill and eat."
B044C010V014	44	10	14	"Not so, my Lord," answered Peter, "for I have never yet eaten anything common and unclean."
B044C010V015	44	10	15	And again a second time came to him a voice, saying, "What God has cleansed you must not call common."
B044C010V016	44	10	16	This happened three times; and immediately the sail was drawn up into the sky.
B044C010V017	44	10	17	Now while Peter was greatly perplexed to know what the vision which he had been sent by Cornelius, and had made inquiries for the house of Simon, stood at the gate,
B044C010V018	44	10	18	and called and asked whether Simon who was called Peter was lodging there.
B044C010V019	44	10	19	So the Spirit said to Peter, who was still pondering over the vision.
B044C010V020	44	10	20	"Three men are now looking for you. Rise, go down and go with them,  nothing doubting; for it is I who have sent them."
B044C010V021	44	10	21	So Peter went down to the men and said. "I am the man you are looking for. What is the reason of your coming?"
B044C010V022	44	10	22	"Cornelius," they answered, "a captain, a devout man, and God-  fearing, of whom the whole, Jewish nation speaks well, was instructed by a holy angel to send for you to come to his house, and to listen to your message."
B044C010V023	44	10	23	So he invited them in and gave them lodging. The next day he rose,  and went off with them, and some of the brothers from Joppa accompanied them;
B044C010V024	44	10	24	and the day after that they reached Caesarea. There Cornelius was waiting for them, and had brought together all his relatives and intimate friends.
B044C010V025	44	10	25	When Peter entered the house Cornelius met him, fell at his feet,  and worshiped him;
B044C010V026	44	10	26	but Peter lifted him up. "Stand up," he said, "I am only a man,  myself."
B044C010V027	44	10	27	And as he talked with him, he went in and found a large company assembled.
B044C010V028	44	10	28	To them he said. "You know, yourselves, that it is illegal for a Jew to associate with or to visit one of another nation; but God has taught me that I should not call any man common or unclean. For this reason, when sent for, I came without demur.
B044C010V029	44	10	29	"I ask therefore why you sent for me."
B044C010V030	44	10	30	Cornelius answered. "Three days ago, at this very hour, I was praying in my house at three oclock in the afternoon, when suddenly a man in a shining robe stood by me,
B044C010V031	44	10	31	and said. "Cornelius, your prayer is heard, and your alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God.
B044C010V032	44	10	32	"So send to Joppa and summon Simon, who is called Peter. He is lodging with Simon the tanner, in a house by the seaside.
B044C010V033	44	10	33	"So I sent for you without delay, and you have been kind enough to come. Now therefore we are all here present in the sight of God, to listen to what the Lord has commanded you to speak."
B044C010V034	44	10	34	Then Peter began to speak. "Of a truth I begin to see quite plainly that God is no respecter of persons;
B044C010V035	44	10	35	"but in every nation he who fears him and works righteousness is acceptable to him.
B044C010V036	44	10	36	"You cannot but know the message which he sent to the descendants of Israel, when he preached the gospel of peace by Jesus Christ who is Lord of all;
B044C010V037	44	10	37	"you know the message spread throughout all Judea, beginning in Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;
B044C010V038	44	10	38	"how God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with power, and how he went about everywhere doing good, and curing all who were oppressed by the devil; for God was with him.
B044C010V039	44	10	39	"And we were witnesses of all that he did, both in the land of the Jews and in Jerusalem. They killed him, hanging him on a tree.
B044C010V040	44	10	40	"But him God raised up on the third day, and permitted him to be made manifest,
B044C010V041	44	10	41	"not to all the people, but to witnesses - men previously chosen by God - that is, to us, who ate and drank with him after he had risen from the dead;
B044C010V042	44	10	42	"when he charged us to preach to the people, and to testify that this was he whom God ordained to be the judge of the living and of the dead.
B044C010V043	44	10	43	"To him all the prophets bear witness, testifying that through his name every one that believes on him will receive remission of sins."
B044C010V044	44	10	44	While Peter was still speaking, the Holy Spirit fell on all who were listening to the message.
