B044C011V001	44	11	1	Now the apostles and the brothers that were in Judea heard that the Gentiles also had received the word of God;
B044C011V002	44	11	2	so, when Peter came up to Jerusalem, the circumcision party disputed with him,
B044C011V003	44	11	3	saying, "You went into the houses of the uncircumcised and ate with them!"
B044C011V004	44	11	4	Then Peter began and explained the whole matter to them in order,  saying.
B044C011V005	44	11	5	"I was in the city of Joppa, praying, and while in a trance I saw a vision; a certain vessel descending, what seemed to be an enormous sail let down to me,
B044C011V006	44	11	6	and while I gazed at it, I examined it carefully, and saw the quadrupeds of the earth and the wild beasts and creeping things and the wild birds.
B044C011V007	44	11	7	I also heard a voice saying to me, Rise, Peter, kill and eat.
B044C011V008	44	11	8	"Not so, my Lord said I, for nothing common or unclean has ever gone into my mouth.
B044C011V009	44	11	9	"But for the second time a voice spoke from the sky, What God has cleansed, you must not call common.
