B066C016V015	66	16	15	Lo, I am coming like a thief. Blessed is the who is on the watch and guarding his clothing, so that he may not walk naked, and they gaze on his shame.
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And the spirits gathered the kings together at the place called in Hebrew, Armageddon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	And the seventh poured out his bowl upon the air, and a great voice came forth out of the temple from the throne, saying, "It is finished!"
B066C016V018	66	16	18	And lightnings and voices and thunders and a great earthquake such as had not happened since man began to be upon the earth, so great an earthquake, so mighty;
B066C016V019	66	16	19	and the great city was shattered into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell, and great Babylon came to mind before the face of God, to give her the cup of the wine of the passion of his anger.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	And every island fled away, and the mountains sank from sight.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And there fell upon men a great hail out of heaven, every stone about the weight of a talent; and men blasphemed God because of the plague of the hail, for the plague of it is very great.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	And there came one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, and spoke to me, saying, "Come hither and I will show you the sentence passed upon the great harlot who sits on many waters,
B066C017V002	66	17	2	with whom the kings of the earth have committed adultery, while all who live on the earth have been made drunken by the wine of her immorality."
B066C017V003	66	17	3	And he bore me away in the Spirit into the desert, and I saw a woman who sat upon a scarlet beast covered with blasphemous names. It had seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	The woman was enwrapped in purple and scarlet and was encrusted with gold and precious stones and pearls. In her hand she held a golden cup filled with abominations, even the impurities of her immorality.
B066C017V005	66	17	5	Upon her forehead a name was written, a mystery, "BABYLON THE GREAT,  THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS, AND ABOMINABLE THINGS OF THE EARTH."
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drunk with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus, and I wondered with a great wonder.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	And the angel said to me. "Why did you wonder? I will explain to you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast with the seven heads and ten horns, that carried her.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw was, and is not, and is about to come up out of the bottomless pit, and to go into perdition. And those who dwell on the earth shall wonder, those whose names have never, from the foundation of the world, been written in the Lambs Book of Life,  when they gaze on the beast; how he was and is not, and is to come.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	Here is the mind that has wisdom. the seven heads are seven hills on which the woman is seated;
B066C017V010	66	17	10	and they are seven kings; the five have fallen, one is, the other is not yet come (and when he does come, he must remain a short time).
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the beast who was, but is not, is himself also an eighth,  although he is one of the seven kings, and is on his way to perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	"The ten horns that you saw are ten kings who have not yet received their kingdoms; but they have received authority as kings for one hour, together with the beast.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These kings have one mind, and they give their power and authority to the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	These will make war against the Lamb, and the Lamb will conquer them, for he is the Lord of lords, and King of kings. And they who are with him are called and faithful and chosen."
B066C017V015	66	17	15	And he also said to me. "The waters which you saw, on which the harlot takes her seat, are peoples and multitudes and nations and tongues.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which you saw, they and the beast will hate the harlot and make her desolate and naked, and will eat her flesh and burn her up with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put it into their hearts to execute his purpose, in executing their common purpose, and by giving over their kingdoms to the beast, until the words of God shall be accomplished.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	The woman whom you saw is the great city which holds sway over the kings of the earth."
B066C018V001	66	18	1	After this I saw another angel coming down from heaven, who had great authority; and the earth was illumined by his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	He shouted with a mighty cry, saying. "She is fallen! She is fallen,  Babylon the great! Now she is a dwelling-place of demons, A stronghold of every foul spirit, A stronghold of every foul and hateful bird.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all nations, having drunk the wine of the frenzy of her fornication, are fallen; And the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, And the merchants of the earth have grown rich by the power of her wantonness."
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And behold I heard another voice from heaven saying. "Come out of her, that you have no fellowship with her sins, And that you receive not her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins have been heaped to heaven, And God has remembered her iniquities.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Render to her what she rendered; Yes, pay double what her deeds deserve. In the cup she mixed, mix double for her.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	By so much as she glorified herself and waxed wanton, By so much give her of torture and tears, For she says in her heart, I sit here a queen, I am no widow. I shall in no wise see mourning.
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore in one day shall these plagues come upon her, Death and mourning and famine, And she shall be burnt with fire; For mighty is the Lord God, her judge.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	And the kings of the earth who committed fornication And lived wantonly with her, Will weep and wail over her, When they behold the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	Standing afar off for the fear of her torment, saying, Woe, woe,  the great city Babylon, the strong city! In one hour is your judgment come!
B066C018V011	66	18	11	"And the merchants of the earth weep and mourn over her, For no one buys their merchandise any more -
B066C018V012	66	18	12	Merchandise of gold and silver and precious stones, Of pearls, and fine linen, and purple and silk and scarlet; All citron wood, and vessels of ivory, And vessels of rare wood and brass and iron and marble;
B066C018V013	66	18	13	Cinnamon and balsam and spices and myrrh and frankincense; Wine and oil and fine flour and wheat; Cattle and sheep, and horses and chariots, And slaves, and the souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	And the fruits which your soul lusted for are gone from you, And all things that were dainty and sumptuous are perished from you, And men shall find them nevermore.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	"The traders in those things, who were enriched by her, shall stand afar off for fear of her torment, weeping and mourning,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	saying. "Woe, woe, the great city! She who was clothed in fine linen and purple and scarlet, And adorned with gold and precious stones and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	In one hour so great riches is made desolate!" And every shipmaster and every one who sails to any port, And sailors, and all seafaring folk,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	Stood at a distance, and as they saw the smoke from the burning city, cried, "What city can compare with the great city?
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they threw dust on their heads, and cried out, Weeping and mourning, saying, "Woe, woe, the great city, In which all who have ships on the sea Grew rich through her luxury! For in one hour she is made desolate!"
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, O Heaven! Rejoice, ye saints, apostles, prophets!  For God has now avenged you.
B066C018V021	66	18	21	Then a mighty angel lifted a boulder like a great millstone, and hurled it into the sea, saying, "So shall Babylon, the great city, be overthrown with a mighty fall, And shall be found no more at all.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	No more shall the voice of harpers and minstrels, flute-players and trumpeters Be heard in you. No more shall any craftsman of any craft Be found at all in you. No more shall the sound of a millstone be heard at all in you.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	No light of a lamp shall ever shine in you again; And in you shall the voice of the bridegroom and of the bride be heard no more. For your merchants were the princes of the earth; And with your sorcery were all the nations deceived;
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in you was found the blood of prophets and of saints, And of all who have been slain upon the earth."
B066C019V001	66	19	1	After this I heard the semblance of the mighty voice of a great multitude in heaven, crying. "Hallelujah! Salvation and glory and power Unto the Lord our God!
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are his judgments; For he has judged the great harlot Who was corrupting the earth with her fornication. On her he has avenged the blood of his slaves."
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And a second time they said. "Allelulia! For the smoke of her torment goes up forever and ever!"
B066C019V004	66	19	4	Then the four and twenty Elders and the four beasts fell down and worshiped God who sits on the throne, saying, "Amen, Hallelujah!"
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And a voice came forth from the throne, saying, "Praise our God, all you his slaves, All you who fear him, small and great!"
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard a sound like the voice of a great multitude, and like the voice of many waters, and like the voice of mighty thunderings,  saying. "Alleluia, for the Lord God omnipotent reigns!
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice and triumph and give him the glory; For the marriage of the Lamb is come, And his bride has made herself ready,
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And it has been granted to her to array herself in fine linen,  bright and pure; For the fine linen is the righteous deeds of the saints."
B066C019V009	66	19	9	And he said to me, Write, "Blessed are those who have been bidden to the marriage supper of the Lamb." And he said to me, "These are true words of God."
B066C019V010	66	19	10	And I fell down at his feet to worship him, and he said to me. "See that you do it not. I am a fellow slave of yours and of your brothers who hold the testimony of Jesus; for the testimony of Jesus is the vital breath of prophecy."
